('188', '80', 'assistant', 'Bulk reassignment of a group of clients from one agent to another can be enabled through administrative bulk actions or batch-processing workflows within the wealth-management platform. The following guidance is aligned with observed patterns around delegation, agent reassignment, and auditability across similar platforms, and is written to be platform-agnostic while citing concrete precedents.\n\n1) Core concept and scope\n- Bulk reassignment is supported as an administrative operation that changes the agent mapping for multiple clients in a single action or batch, rather than reassigning clients individually. This aligns with established delegation and handover capabilities where a new agent can be designated for a set of clients (and customers may receive notifications when reassignment occurs) [1].\n- The operation typically results in updating each client’s primary agent/ownership reference and related entitlements, and it may drive downstream workflow changes (e.g., order routing, compliance checks, and client communications) consistent with the platform’s change-management policies [1].\n\n2) Permissions and governance\n- Access to bulk reassignment features is governed by role-based access controls (RBAC) or equivalent entitlement systems. Ensure the Operations role has the required permissions to perform agent reassignment and to view/modify client-agent mappings [3].\n- Changes should be auditable and traceable; system logs should capture who initiated the bulk action, when, what scope (client subset or full batch), and the before/after agent mappings [2].\n\n3) Data requirements and eligibility\n- The operation requires clear identifiers for the source agent and the destination agent, and a list or criteria identifying which client records are to be reassigned (client/investment account identifiers or equivalent primary keys). In practice, identifiers used for client-agent mapping are treated as the authoritative keys for reassignment [3].\n- Ensure all clients in scope are eligible for reassignment under policy (e.g., entitlements, regulatory/compliance constraints, and any client-level approvals). The platform should validate these before finalizing the bulk action [3].\n\n4) Bulk action approaches (UI and API)\n- UI approach (bulk action): Admin or Operations consoles commonly provide a Bulk Reassignment feature. The steps generally include selecting the bulk action, specifying source and destination agents, defining the target client scope (e.g., via a filter, batch import, or pre-defined group), validating the scope, and executing the reassignment. Post-action, a confirmation and audit trail are produced, and notifications may be issued to clients per policy [1].\n- API/batch approach: For automated or integrated workflows, an API or batch job can be invoked to perform the reassignment in bulk. The API would accept sourceAgentId, destinationAgentId, and a list of client identifiers (or an alternative scope descriptor). The system should return a batch job/operation ID for tracking and provide an audit trail on completion [2].\n\n5) Post-action notifications and client impact\n- Clients may receive notifications about their reassignment to a new agent, depending on policy. When such notifications are configured, there should be an automated mechanism to alert the client about the change of agent/relationship owner [1].\n- Downstream workflow implications can include updated advisor dashboards, order routing recalculations, and re-validation steps to ensure ongoing compliance and alignment with risk/approach profiles [1].\n\n6) Auditing, rollback, and compliance considerations\n- All bulk reassignment activities should be logged with sufficient detail to support audits, including who performed the action, the scope, timestamps, and before/after mappings. This supports traceability and regulatory review [2].\n- Where feasible, include rollback or compensating actions to revert the reassignment if a subsequent review or error is detected. This capability should be part of the platform’s change-management and auditing framework [2].\n- Permissions and changes should be captured in the entitlements and access-control framework to ensure only authorized users can perform bulk reassignments, and that changes stay within compliance guidelines [3].\n\n7) Related considerations and examples\n- Delegation and handover concepts exist in practice where an agent is reassigned to a client, with administrative notifications to clients upon reassignment [1].\n- Individual changes to a client’s agent mapping (e.g., editing a customer profile to update the Primary Agent) illustrate the fundamental operation of reassigning ownership at the client level, which bulk operations extend to the multi-record case [4].\n\nSources:\n- Maybank_Handover and Delegation_V12_CCV10.pdf [1]\n- BOC Philippines Tech - Trust systems.pdf [2]\n- EID031 - Model Portfolio_Basket Based Investments.docx [3]\n- Maybank_Journey of Editing Customer Profile_V12_CCV10.pdf [4]', '8938773f-9a4a-47b9-8be0-9d4f5d660966', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["RM","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","CIF id","securities","warning message","security","Mutual Funds"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:order","dataentity:cif_id","dataentity:securities","dataentity:security","dataentity:warning_message","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:customer","dataentity:rm","system:rmws","report:warning_message","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:transaction"],"expanded_nodes":95,"expanded_edges":254,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually?","How can an Operations User perform a bulk reassignment of multiple client records to a different agent without selecting each client individually?","Within the wealth-management platform, what options exist for an Operations User to bulk-transfer multiple client records from one agent to another without per-client selection? Provide guidance on supported bulk actions, required permissions, eligible client criteria, batch size limits, data requirements (source and destination agent identifiers, client IDs), steps via UI or API, and considerations for auditing, rollback, and impact on related workflows and compliance.","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually? Supervisor’s queue","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually? Estimated Units","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually? Introduction","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually? Model Portfolio Maintenance","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually? General Validation","Order DISPLAYED_ON nomination form","Order MAPS_TO PG","Order MAPS_TO STP","customer FEEDS Order"],"kg_vector_store_id":"vs_6934751b8a90819190113fe85b689848","doc_vector_store_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","intent_route":"hybrid","intent_hops":2,"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","response_id":"8938773f-9a4a-47b9-8be0-9d4f5d660966","is_conversational":false,"processing_time_seconds":105.95,"request_id":"21b85e95-004a-4079-8a11-94949cc2a91c","domainResolution":{"domainId":"wealth_management","strategy":"fallback","confidence":0,"matchedKeywords":[]}}', '2025-12-16 06:15:09.346455'),
('191', '81', 'user', 'How can a user automatically generate a list of target leads based on specific customer criteria?', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-12-16 06:37:11.013528'),
('192', '81', 'assistant', '# Automated generation of target leads from defined customer criteria\n\n## Overview\n- Lead generation is achieved by filtering existing customers through rule-based criteria (lead rules) to produce a target list for campaigns or outreach. This capability is described in lead list management workflows, including automatic lead generation and the ability to generate lists from defined rules [1].\n\n## Data sources to power lead generation\n- Primary source: the set of existing customers in the wealth management system, from which leads are filtered according to rules [2].\n- Customer risk context: risk profile questionnaire data and the related risk-questionnaire maintenance/context inform how customers can be segmented or prioritized within lead rules [3].\n\n## Defining the criteria (lead rules)\n- Create and configure lead rules that define filter criteria to identify potential targets from the existing customer base. Lead rules can be added, viewed, modified, and used to generate lists (leading to campaign targeting) [2].\n- Rule definitions typically encapsulate the target attributes (e.g., risk tier, asset metrics, location, and other customer attributes) and can be adjusted over time to refine targeting [2].\n\n## Scoring, deduplication, and list management\n- Lead-rule workflows support management actions such as viewing, adding, modifying, and generating lists; advanced workflows may include merging lists to consolidate duplicates or complementary segments (deduplication/merging behavior is indicated by lead-list management capabilities) [2].\n\n## Export and integration with CRM/marketing tools\n- Generated lead lists can be used to drive campaigns and other CRM/marketing activities, enabling export or direct use within campaign workflows and related tools [3].\n\n## Typical workflow (high level)\n1) Define lead criteria as a lead rule (e.g., risk profile band, AUM thresholds, geography, demographics, engagement signals). [2]  \n2) Save and configure the rule, then run Generate List to produce the target-lead set from existing customers. [2]  \n3) Review, adjust, and (if needed) merge/deduplicate multiple lead lists to ensure a clean target set. [2]  \n4) Export the resulting lead list to CRM/marketing tools or use it to drive a campaign in the platform. [3]\n\n## Governance and approvals\n- Changes to lead rules themselves may be governed by standard controls in the platform environment, with downstream approvals managed via the same governance processes that manage risk-profile and questionnaire configurations in related journeys. See risk-profile and lead-management governance patterns in the referenced documents for context. [1][3]\n\n---\nSources: HSBC_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV13docx.pdf; JBR_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV10docx.pdf; HSBC_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V11_CCV10.pdf', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["INVESTOR","RM","customer","risk profiling","Customer Risk profile","Risk Profile Questionnaire","Analytics","Key metrics","Projections","Exposures"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:risk_profile_questionnaire","compliance:risk_profiling","system:rmws","dataentity:projections","aum:risk_profiling","dataentity:investor","report:risk_profile_questionnaire","dataentity:risk_profiling","report:exposures","dataentity:analytics","dataentity:rm","system:analytics","dataentity:customer","dataentity:key_metrics","dataentity:exposures","aum:customer_risk_profile"],"expanded_nodes":43,"expanded_edges":57,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user automatically generate a list of target leads based on specific customer criteria?","How can we automatically generate a list of target leads by applying defined customer criteria within the wealth-management platform, including criteria definition, data sources, scoring, and integration options with CRM/marketing tools?","What configuration or workflow enables automatic generation of a target-lead list by applying defined customer criteria (risk profile, AUM, geography, demographics, engagement history), including data sources, rules, scoring, deduplication, and export to CRM/marketing tools?","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user automatically generate a list of target leads based on specific customer criteria? risk profiling","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user automatically generate a list of target leads based on specific customer criteria? Name","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question