('153', '65', 'user', 'what is CRR and PRR?', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-12-13 18:25:58.06439'),
('154', '65', 'assistant', 'CRR and PRR are two linked risk metrics used to govern investment actions in risk-rating and portfolio-risk workflows.\n\nCRR: Customer Risk Rating\n- What it stands for: CRR is the numeric rating assigned to a customer based on the customer’s risk profile (i.e., the customer-side risk appetite and capacity that drive investment decisions) [1].\n- What it is derived from: CRR is derived from the Customer Risk Profile, which encapsulates the investor’s risk tolerance and related factors used to categorize risk at the client level [1].\n- How it is displayed and used: CRR is expressed as a numerical risk code (1–6) in risk-related screens and reports, aligning with product risk displays and risk filters in the system’s user interfaces [3].\n\nPRR: Product Risk Rating\n- What it stands for: PRR is the numeric rating assigned to a product (or security) reflecting its risk level, derived from the product’s Risk Profile and displayed as a risk code (1–6) [1].\n- What it is derived from: PRR is derived from the Product Risk Profile (the product’s own risk characteristics) and is compared directly to the customer’s CRR in risk-workflows [1].\n- How it is displayed and used: PRR is shown as a numeric risk code (1–6) in risk-related screens (e.g., Product Selection Screen) and in risk-focused reports; products are filtered or flagged according to their PRR in relation to the customer’s CRR [3].\n\nHow CRR and PRR interact in risk workflows\n- Risk alignment checks: When PRR equals CRR + 2, the system raises a caution/warning to the user to confirm the increment in product risk relative to the customer’s risk rating [1].\n- Hard stops: If PRR > CRR + 2 (i.e., product risk is more than two levels higher than the customer’s risk rating), the system enforces a hard stop and blocks the transaction, preventing inappropriate risk exposure [1].\n- Focused vs Other funds behavior: The product list differentiates Focused Funds (PRR <= CRR) from Other Funds (PRR > CRR); only Focused Funds are typically eligible for certain actions, while Other Funds may be gated or require additional review [2].\n- Display and interpretation: Across screens (e.g., Product Selection Screen, risk dashboards, and transaction reports), risk is presented using numerical codes (1–6) rather than descriptive text to support consistent risk assessment and automated decisioning; this coding is emphasized in risk-deviation and risk-rating workflows [3].\n\nKey data sources and screens\n- Data sources: Customer Risk Profile (for CRR) and Product Risk Profile (for PRR); both are used to generate the 1–6 risk codes that populate risk screens and decision logic [1][3].\n- Screens and displays: Product Selection Screen and related product risk displays show risk codes; risk-rating-related screens, reports, and overlays (e.g., risk warnings, product risk class displays) use the 1–6 scale to communicate risk and to drive gating rules [3].\n\nImpact on client risk classification and recommendations\n- Alignment rule implications: If PRR is within one level of CRR (or equal/less), no warning is issued; a mismatch of one level prompts a warning, and a mismatch of two levels prompts a warning with review, while a mismatch greater than two levels results in a hard stop. This ensures client risk classifications and investment recommendations stay within acceptable risk boundaries defined by the customer’s risk appetite [1][2].\n- Portfolio construction guidance: Since PRR and CRR govern eligibility and gating (e.g., Focused Funds vs Other Funds), they directly influence which investments are considered suitable for a given client and thus affect recommendations and approved portfolios [2].\n\nIn short, CRR and PRR provide a quantified, codified risk alignment mechanism between a client’s risk appetite (CRR) and a product’s risk characteristics (PRR). They are computed from the respective risk profiles, expressed on a 1–6 scale, and drive warnings, hard stops, and eligible product sets within risk-rating and portfolio-risk workflows to protect clients from misaligned investments [1][2][3].\n\nSources\n- 360ONE_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV13_Part 2.pdf\n- Maybank_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_V12_CCV10_Part 2.pdf\n- SBI_Journey of Assesing Risk_Deviation document.pdf', '336d8176-820b-4077-95eb-dae89a244e4d', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Risk Rating","INVESTOR","RM","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","Mutual Funds","Risk Appetite Mapping","Portfolio Performance Report"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:risk_appetite_mapping","dataentity:investor","report:pf_performance_report","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:transaction","dataentity:risk_rating","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:order","system:rmws","dataentity:customer","dataentity:rm","system:risk_appetite_mapping"],"expanded_nodes":70,"expanded_edges":177,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR?","What do CRR and PRR refer to in this wealth-management platform, and how are they defined and used within risk-rating and portfolio-risk workflows?","Provide precise definitions for CRR and PRR as used in the wealth-management platform, including what each acronym stands for, how each is determined or calculated, which data sources and risk-related screens they relate to (e.g., Risk Rating, Customer Risk profile, Product risk profile), where they are displayed (screens and reports such as Portfolio Performance Report), and how they influence client risk classification or investment recommendations.","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR? Doctype","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR? Product Card-Nominee Details","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR? RTA REF NO.","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR? Scheme name","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is CRR and PRR? Name","Switch PROCESSES Mutual Funds","Mutual Funds VALIDATES Switch","Mutual Funds CONTAINS Product risk profile","PRODUCT SELECTION SCREEN DISPLAYED_ON Mutual Funds"],"kg_vector_store_id":"vs_6934751b8a90819190113fe85b689848","doc_vector_store_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","intent_route":"hybrid","intent_hops":2,"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","response_id":"336d8176-820b-4077-95eb-dae89a244e4d","is_conversational":false,"processing_time_seconds":98.84,"request_id":"d021b416-cf2c-40e8-aba0-e4cb59423bbd","domainResolution":{"domainId":"wealth_management","strategy":"fallback","confidence":0,"matchedKeywords":[]}}', '2025-12-13 18:25:58.323055'),
