('28', '9', 'assistant', '# **KG + VectorStore Answer - [Focused Response Directive]\n\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\n\nUser''s Question: What is the CRR and PRR logic for order placement?**\n\n_Generated: 2025-10-22 07:42_\n\n## **Answer**\n\n**Direct Answer:**  \nPRR is compared with CRR during order placement; if PRR equals CRR+2, escalation occurs. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>  \nEscalation moves to Circle head, then Zonal head, and finally to Supervisor for authorization. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>  \nRMWS shows a warning when PRR equals CRR+2 before proceeding. <sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup>  \nIf PRR exceeds CRR+2, the system hard stops the transaction. <sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup> <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n**Key Points:**  \n• Point 1: PRR vs CRR rule is PRR = CRR+2 triggers escalation. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>  \n• Point 2: Escalation path is Circle head → Zonal head → Supervisor; RMWS warns at PRR=CRR+2. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup>  \n• Point 3: PRR > CRR+2 yields a hard stop; no transaction allowed. <sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup>\n\n**Note:** The described logic applies to Purchase, Switch, SIP, and STP orders. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n---\n\n## **Citations**\n\n<a id="cite-1"></a>\n**[1]** → **Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_Base_V1.0.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-2"></a>\n**[2]** → **OMS_ProductFitment_Doc_UNB_Ver1.4.docx.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-3"></a>\n**[3]** → **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF  V1.0_SBI_...**\n\n<a id="cite-4"></a>\n**[4]** → **PAD PMS Reports & Statements_Final.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-5"></a>\n**[5]** → **PAD PMS Reports & Statements_Final [v1].pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-6"></a>\n**[6]** → **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_IIFL_V1.1_...**\n\n\n---\n\n## **Sources by File**\n\n- **Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_Base_V1.0.pdf** → [1]\n- **OMS_ProductFitment_Doc_UNB_Ver1.4.docx.pdf** → [2]\n- **PAD PMS Reports & Statements_Final [v1].pdf** → [5]\n- **PAD PMS Reports & Statements_Final.pdf** → [4]\n- **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF  V1.0_SBI_...** → [3]\n- **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_IIFL_V1.1_...** → [6]\n', 'a91169ae-ed63-44f5-bc17-396792ca4088', '[{"filename":"Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_Base_V1.0.pdf","file_id":"file-NXXP1XvZD1dQwrRs726Wde","score":0.7619279779957363,"text":"2. If the Product Risk Profile is 2 levels higher than the Customer Risk Profile (PRR=CRR+2). The Order will go \\nfirst to Circle head/ Zonal head for approval and after they have approved the order will go for further \\nauthorization to the Supervisor. This is applicable for Purchase, Switch, SIP and STP transactions \\n\\n3. To authorize an order, supervisor needs to log in to the application and click on the supervisor approval icon \\n\\n in the top panel  \\n\\n4. The supervisor then selects “Order Authorization” from the drop down in the Supervisor Approval screen \\n\\nInternal to HSBC and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 62 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                             \\n \\n\\n \\n\\nScreen: Supervisor selects Order Authorization from the dropdown \\n\\n5. Once selected, the list of orders currently pending for approval is displayed \\n\\n6. Supervisor can search for a specific card by entering the Order Number/Scheme Name/Customer Name \\n\\n \\n\\nScreen: List of orders currently pending for approval \\n\\n7. To further filter the list, supervisor has access to the following filter criteria: \\n\\na. Transaction Type  – Allows the supervisor to filter based on the Transaction Type  \\n\\nInternal to HSBC and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 63 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                             \\n \\n\\nb. User Name – Allows the supervisor to filter as per the User’s \\n\\n \\n\\nScreen: Filter by Transaction Type and/or User Name \\n\\n8. Supervisor can click on the Order Card to expand it and then click on “Claim”. Once an order is claimed, the \\n\\npending order will be moved from the ”Pending Approval Listing” (common queue)  to “To Approve Listing” \\n\\n(supervisor’s personal approval queue) \\n\\n \\n\\nScreen: Supervisor selects the desired order and clicks on Claim \\n\\nInternal to HSBC and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 64 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                             \\n \\n\\n9. To access t...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What is the CRR and PRR logic for order placement? process workflow steps","norm_score":1,"relevance_score":0.6605374822949083},{"filename":"OMS_ProductFitment_Doc_UNB_Ver1.4.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-ER4Vq5EKXkkvbhiNtP8ZTa","score":0.7426091090915894,"text":"iv. Business Rules: \\na) Subscription orders can only be placed if investor has adequate cash balance in \\n\\nhis/her cash account. \\nb) In case of change in FX Rate or Fee, SMS will be sent to Head of RM. Ops needs to \\n\\nvalidate if approval has been obtained and approval document needs to be \\nuploaded in the system. \\n\\nv. Actor / Entitlements: \\na) Relationship Manager \\nb) Branch Teller \\n\\nvi. Trigger: Manual \\nvii. Output Details: Orders, Trades, Position \\n\\nviii. Alerts: Alert to be generated in case there is a change in FX Rate, Fee Override \\nix. Notification: None \\n\\n \\n5. Next Process – None \\n\\n \\n6. Process Gaps -  \\n\\ni. Lien to be marked with a Buffer for unit based orders \\n \\n \\n\\n7.  \\n\\n15 | Page \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                \\n\\nProcess ID_1.2 – Order Flow – Equity / FI / ETF / SP \\n\\n \\n1. Process Objective – The objective of this process is to capture orders, place, execute, confirm and settle. The \\n\\norder flow being discussed is only for Equity, Bonds, ETF and Structured Products. \\n \\n\\n2. Process Flow to Module Mapping:  \\n\\nProcess Area Process Sub Process Intellect Module Intellect Process Name \\n\\nOrder \\nManagement \\nSystem Order Flow   OMS Order Management \\n\\n \\n3. Process Flow Diagram: \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\nProcess ID_1.2a – Order Initiation \\n\\n \\n\\n16 | Page \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                \\n\\n \\n\\n \\nProcess ID_1.2b – Order Routing \\n\\n4. Description of process steps –  \\na. Process Description: \\n\\ni. Orders for Fixed Income/Equity/ETF/Structured Product instrument can be initiated by \\nRelationship Manager, ISD, AMD or Treasury. \\n\\nii. The investment request may come through mail, fax or call from investor. In case of DPM \\ncustomers and Proprietary Funds, AMD will initiate the orders. \\n\\niii. For NDPMS portfolios, system will check for Communication Indemnity document in case \\nMode of Instruction is Mail, Fax or Telephone. \\n\\niv. During Order capture process, the document submission status and document expiry date will \\nbe validated by OMS. List of Documents for FI/Equity is as follows: \\nDocument Expiry Date Validation: \\nW8 Ben \\nFATCA \\nLeverage \\nPassport \\nEmirates ID \\nPOA \\n \\nDocument Submission Status: \\nLeverage Agreement - Leverage Orders \\nRisk Profile Document \\n\\n17 | Page...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What is the CRR and PRR logic for order placement? requirements rules conditions","norm_score":0.7753728190227938,"relevance_score":0.5801710695925013},{"filename":"WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF  V1.0_SBI_CCV1.3.pdf","file_id":"file-TMMZJ9hfChbHUJMwwK3zbC","score":0.728589668475767,"text":"7. If the RMWS does the order journey and the Product Risk Profile is only  2 level up than the Customer Risk \\nProfile  (PRR=CRR+2) ,then the system will throw a warning displayed to the RMWS prompting him to \\nconfirm the same. All the securities where there is a mismatch would be shown in the pop-up \\nmessage.(applicable for Purchase and Switch transaction type). Through the client portal this deviation \\nwill be hard Stop.Customer would not be able to place order. \\n\\n8. In the above scenario when the RM will submit the order for authorization then the Order will go first to \\nCircle head/ Zonal head for approval and after they have approved the order will go for further \\nauthorization to RMWS. \\n\\n9. If in RM or client order journey Product Risk Profile is greater than Customer Risk Profile +2, (PRR>CRR+2) \\nfor Ex- customer risk profile is Very Conservative then he cannot buy a product whose risk profile is \\nAggressive and Very aggressive. System will throw a hard stop and should not allow Transacting in this \\nsecurity through the RM office or Client portal. \\n\\n10. User is able to see the validations while placing the Purchase transaction on min Purchase amount/quantity \\n\\nas maintained for selected security. \\n\\nInternal to Customer and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 16 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                             \\n \\n\\n11. RMWS  will cancel/ Confirm the risk notification and then proceed to the product summary screen. \\n\\n2.1.1.1.1. Confirm the Selected Products \\n \\n\\n1. In the product summary screen, the customer can review the securities selected. If the customer wishes to \\n\\nchange any details, they can click on the “Back” button to navigate back to the “Select the Products” \\n\\nsection. To proceed ahead, the user clicks on the “Confirm” button. \\n\\n2. User clicks on the “Confirm” button to navigate to the “ Product Cart ” screen. \\n\\n \\nScreen: Summary of Securities Selected by the User \\n\\n2.1.2. Selection of Investment Account \\n\\n1. User selects the desired investment account(s) from the dropdown and also selects the folio number from \\n