omer Risk\\nReport Purpose This report captures the Product Risk vs. Customer Risk (mismatch) alerts that \\n\\nhas been triggered on PMS. User will be able to see the list of customers of \\nwhich this alert has been triggered on based on the report selection criteria\\n\\nReport Selection Criteria \\n(This will appear as input fields\\nfor generating the report)\\n\\n Alert Date (Period)\\nClient (searchable field by name, ID or CIF)\\nCustomer Segment\\nSales Staff (this is for supervisor only and all the sales staff who reports the \\n\\nlogged in user will display in the drop-down field)\\nReport Sorting Sequence By default, records are grouped and sorted by sales staff name (ascending), \\n\\nCustomer name (ascending), date (ascending)\\nReport Page Break 50\\nDistribution Report can be exported in excel format\\nReport Frequency Ad hoc (as and when downloaded)\\nReport Ad Hoc Request Yes\\nReport Format Excel\\nCountry / Entity MY,SG, TH\\nAccess Access to report subject to user access matrix\\nRemarks Date Stamp (of as at when report is downloaded) should be stated\\n\\nField Description...","query":"customer risk rating product risk rating","norm_score":0.9477965841110451,"relevance_score":0.5180219507807204},{"filename":"PAD PMS Reports & Statements_Final [v1].pdf","file_id":"file-JgsP8m2fi4WuYcRe3VVhwG","score":0.753417799262505,"text":"Corporate Customer: Company Name in English alphabet \\nCustomer Name (TH) [Applicable to Thailand]\\n\\nIndividual Customer: Full Name in Thai Text\\n\\nCorporate Customer: Company Name in Thai Text\\n\\nCustomer Segment\\n[Indicator]\\nMass/ Prime / Preferred/ Private / Corporate (as reflected in Country \\nSource Data)\\n\\nCurrent Risk Profile\\nCurrent Risk Profile Result (Outcome of Questionnaire)\\n- Defensive/Aggressive/etc..\\n\\nPrevious Risk Profile\\nPrevious Risk Profile Result (Outcome of Questionnaire)\\n- Defensive/Aggressive/etc..\\n\\nTagged Sales Staff ID Staff ID (as reflected in source) of staff customer tagged to\\nTagged Sales Staff Name Staff name (as reflected in source) of staff customer tagged to in English \\n\\nTagged Sales Staff Supervisor Name Supervisor name  (as reflected in user access matrix -staff \\nhierarcy/relationship  ) of staff customer tagged to in English text\\n\\nTagged Sales Staff Supervisor Staff ID Supervisor staff ID (as reflected in user access matrix -staff \\nhierarcy/relationship  ) of staff customer tagged to\\n\\nTagged Sales Staff Region Region or Zone (as reflected in user access matrix -staff \\nhierarcy/relationship  ) of staff customer tagged to \\n\\nConfidential to CIMB and Intellect                                                                                                                                         Page 35\\n\\n\\n\\n4.9.3 AL003 – Product Risk vs. Customer Risk\\n\\nReport Name Alerts Report - Product Risk vs. Customer Risk\\nReport Purpose This report captures the Product Risk vs. Customer Risk (mismatch) alerts that \\n\\nhas been triggered on PMS. User will be able to see the list of customers of \\nwhich this alert has been triggered on based on the report selection criteria\\n\\nReport Selection Criteria \\n(This will appear as input fields\\nfor generating the report)\\n\\n Alert Date (Period)\\nClient (searchable field by name, ID or CIF)\\nCustomer Segment\\nSales Staff (this is for supervisor only and all the sales staff who reports the \\n\\nlogged in user will display in the drop-down field)\\nReport Sorting Sequence By default, records are grouped and sorted by sales staff name (ascending), \\n\\nCustomer name (ascending), date (ascending)\\nReport Page Break 50\\nDistribution Report can be exported in excel format\\nReport Frequency Ad hoc (as and when downloaded)\\nReport Ad Hoc Request Yes\\nReport Format Excel\\nCountry / Entity MY,SG, TH\\nAccess Access to report subject to user access matrix\\nRemarks Date Stamp (of as at when report is downloaded) should be stated\\n\\nField Description...","query":"customer risk rating product risk rating","norm_score":0.9010492038668171,"relevance_score":0.503997736707452},{"filename":"WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF_IIFL_V1.1_CCV.1.4_Part 3.pdf","file_id":"file-3kiJU4x7wQm66p8BFFvyqM","score":0.694892020342197,"text":"Internal to IIFL and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 39\\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                            \\n\\n4. If  Customer  has  invested in  the same fund using  multiple  folios  then the  same security  card  will  be\\ndisplayed  multiple  times  with  the  folio  number.  Cards  will  be  displayed  with  Security  and  Folio\\ncombination. Hence for each card Units and Current Market Value will be displayed as per folio\\n\\n9.3. Product Selection Summary\\nProduct Comparison, Product Additional Details in Overlay details have been explained in the Purchase section (Refer\\nto 4.3 Product Selection Summary section in this document)\\n\\n1. User lands on the product selection summary screen. User will be able to see the securities which were\\nselected in the Product Selection screen\\n\\n2. User  clicks  on  the  transaction  dropdown  of  the  selected  security.  Selected  transaction  type  will  be\\n“Systematic Transfer Plan” and User enters the STP Amount and selects the Switch In Fund. User will click on\\nthe “Next” button at the bottom right of the screen\\n\\nScreen: Select STP transaction\\n\\n3. User will be able to see the validations while placing the STP transaction on min STP amount as maintained\\nfor selected security. (Refer Validations section)\\n\\n4. If the customer does not have a risk profile or the risk profile has expired, the system prompts the user to\\nselect “Yes” or “No” option. If the user selects “Yes”, the system returns to the product selection screen and\\nallows only redemption transactions. If the user selects “No”, the system returns to the product selection\\nsummary screen and the user needs to perform risk profiling for the customer to proceed further\\n\\nInternal to IIFL and Intellect                                                                                                                                                        Page 40\\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                            \\n\\nScreen: Notification to User when Customer does not have Risk Profile or Risk Profile has Expired\\n\\n5. If the Switch In Fund Risk Profile is equal to or less than the Customer Risk profile then no warning message\\nwill be displayed and User can complete the order journey (applicable for...","query":"risk profile comparison order placement","norm_score":0.22054969850799117,"relevance_score":0.3100495512563153}]', '{"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_689b49252a4c8191a12a1528a475fbd8","response_id":"a91169ae-ed63-44f5-bc17-396792ca4088","is_conversational":false,"mode":"concise","processing_time_seconds":83.55,"request_id":"90005ea1-8bd4-4502-a044-52612b268464"}', '2025-10-22 07:42:07.452795'),
