ilable in the application? Max Drawdown","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What are rhe portfolio return parameters available in the application? Product risk profile","transaction FEEDS RTA","IWMS READS_FROM transaction","SAB VALIDATES transaction","folio CONTAINS transaction"],"kg_vector_store_id":"vs_6934751b8a90819190113fe85b689848","doc_vector_store_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","intent_route":"hybrid","intent_hops":2,"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","response_id":"ce42e3f7-5f13-4daf-a705-2d467fdbc35c","is_conversational":false,"processing_time_seconds":64.06,"request_id":"30d3d64b-7ffb-452d-8e17-000b4ef9cf39","domainResolution":{"domainId":"wealth_management","strategy":"classifier","confidence":0.08,"matchedKeywords":["portfolio"]}}', '2025-12-13 20:43:43.522323'),
('196', '81', 'assistant', '## End-to-End capability: campaigns and customer feedback\n\n### Objective\n- Provide a generic, platform-agnostic approach to monitor active campaigns and capture customer feedback, linking feedback to the relevant campaign and customer, and enabling analytics on progress and engagement. This aligns with documented capabilities to view campaign dashboards, track metrics for active campaigns, and capture feedback via calendar or customer-facing screens.\n\n### 1) Core capabilities\n- Campaign progress tracking\n  - Maintain visibility of active campaigns with status, stages, milestones, deadlines, and associated key metrics. The Campaign Dashboard enables viewing and tracking metrics for active campaigns tagged to the user, supporting quick assessment of progress and bottlenecks [1].\n- Feedback capture\n  - Record customer feedback related to a campaign through screens like Feedback(Calendar) or Feedback(Customer Dashboard), with the ability to save feedback entries. Screens exist to navigate to feedback and save it, indicating structured capture tied to the campaign context [2], and similar capabilities exist for customer-facing dashboards and calendars [3].\n- End-to-end linkage\n  - Feedback records should be linked to both the campaign and the customer to ensure traceability and impact analysis (e.g., feedback captured from a calendar or a customer-facing dashboard and associated with the corresponding campaign) [2], [3].\n- Validation and governance\n  - Campaign and feedback capture flows include mandatory field verification and validation steps to ensure data quality during capture [2].\n- Communications and lifecycle events\n  - Campaigns support communications within the defined campaign window (start to end) and related lifecycle actions (e.g., capture feedback, view dashboards) as part of the end-to-end experience [4], [5].\n\n### 2) Recommended screens and workflows\n- Campaign Dashboard (monitoring screen)\n  - Purpose: view and track all metrics for active campaigns assigned to the user; navigate to feedback capture as needed [1].\n- Capture Feedback (feedback entry screen)\n  - Purpose: record customer feedback tied to a specific campaign, typically including text/narrative and optional structured fields; supports saving entries and timestamping [2], [3].\n- Feedback Calendar / Customer Dashboard feedback view\n  - Purpose: provide calendar-based or dashboard-based entry points for recording feedback, with save/confirm actions to persist feedback [2], [3].\n- Campaign Communication screen (optional within campaign workflow)\n  - Purpose: manage campaign communications within the timeline (start date to end date), illustrating end-to-end campaign orchestration alongside feedback capture [4].\n\n### 3) Data model and linkage (conceptual guidance)\n- Primary entities and linkage\n  - Campaign: the overarching initiative with status, stages, milestones, deadlines, and metrics.\n  - Feedback: records created to capture customer input related to a campaign; each feedback item is linked to a campaign and a customer to establish context and enable analytics.\n  - Customer: the individual or entity providing feedback, for whom the campaign is relevant.\n  - Linkage principle: feedback records reference campaign_id and customer_id to establish a direct association with the campaign and the customer (enabling end-to-end traceability in dashboards and analytics).\n- Evidence from documented flows\n  - Campaign dashboards exist to view and track metrics for active campaigns, establishing the need for ongoing status monitoring [1].\n  - Feedback can be captured via calendar or customer-facing screens with a Save action, demonstrating structured recording of customer input linked to the campaign [2], [3].\n  - Campaign communications are managed within the campaign window, illustrating end-to-end process boundaries and interactions with campaign data [4], [5].\n\n### 4) Validation, data quality, and governance\n- Validation rules\n  - Ensure mandatory fields are completed during feedback capture (e.g., at least the feedback content and timestamp) to maintain data integrity [2].\n- Data integrity and governance\n  - Feedback and campaign data should be maintained within the same lifecycle and governance boundaries as other campaign artifacts, supporting consistent reporting and auditability [4], [5].\n\n### 5) Analytics and views to assess performance and engagement\n- Campaign-level analytics\n  - Dashboards should present status, progress against milestones, upcoming deadlines, and key campaign KPIs to enable proactive management [1].\n- Feedback analytics\n  - Aggregated feedback metrics (volume, sentiment, rating distribution, trends over time) should be available to assess customer engagement and campaign effectiveness; capability to view feedback through calendar/customer dashboards supports ongoing monitoring [2], [3].\n\n### 6) Summary mapping to documented capabilities\n- Campaign Dashboard: view and track metrics for active campaigns; navigate to capture feedback [1].\n- Feedback capture: calendars or customer dashboards allow recording feedback with a save action [2], [3].\n- Communications and lifecycle: campaign communications within the start/end window and broader campaign management steps support a complete end-to-end flow [4], [5].\n\nSources\n- SBI_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV13.pdf\n- SBI_Journey of RM from Customer Meeting to Closure of Action Items_V10.pdf\n- SBI International_Journey of RM from Customer Meeting to Closure of Action Items_V10.pdf\n- 360One_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV10docx.pdf\n- HSBC_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV13docx.pdf', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Customer Dashboard","Product Cart","Flow Diagram","Journey from Order Placement till Settlement","Prerequisite","Risk Profile Deviation alert","Product risk profile","Mutual Funds","SIP Scheduler","Analytics"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:warning_message","report:prerequisite","datastore:product_cart","system:product_cart","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:analytics","report:customer_dashboard","system:analytics","report:risk_profile_deviation_alert","report:flow_diagram","dataentity:product_cart","report:product_cart","system:sip_scheduler","report:journey_from_order_placement_till_settlement"],"expanded_nodes":42,"expanded_edges":78,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user track the progress of active campaigns and record specific feedback from customers?","How would a user formulate a generic approach to monitor the status of active campaigns and capture customer feedback associated with those campaigns, in a business-agnostic way?","Describe the end-to-end capability set for monitoring progress of active campaigns (including status, stages, milestones, deadlines, and key metrics) and for recording customer fe