 pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user track the progress of active campaigns and record specific feedback from customers? PRODUCT SELECTION SCREEN","PRODUCT SELECTION SCREEN VALIDATES Prerequisite","Login GOVERNED_BY Prerequisite","warning message CALCULATES SIP","Prerequisite VALIDATES Order","Prerequisite VALIDATES Product risk profile"],"kg_vector_store_id":"vs_6934751b8a90819190113fe85b689848","doc_vector_store_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","intent_route":"hybrid","intent_hops":2,"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","response_id":"9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176","is_conversational":true,"previous_response_id":"9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176","processing_time_seconds":102.12,"request_id":"0b506922-d2b7-4e87-9dd2-ad44d4c2cbaa","domainResolution":{"domainId":"wealth_management","strategy":"conversation","confidence":1,"matchedKeywords":[]}}', '2025-12-16 06:45:19.736427'),
('207', '81', 'user', 'How can a supervisor drill down from the high-level lead summary to view the performance of individual Relationship Managers?', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-12-16 07:08:12.267839'),
('208', '81', 'assistant', 'Drill-down path from Lead Summary to per-RM performance\n\n1) Start at the Lead Summary (Supervisor view)\n- The supervisor-page presents leads grouped by Relationship Manager (RM), showing per-RM lead counts and statuses. You can search by RM name and filter by lead status, then open a RM-specific view by selecting the three-dots action on a RM row to see detailed metrics for that RM. This provides an at-a-glance view of each RM’s activity and lead progress. [1]\n\n2) Access the hierarchical RM view to select an individual RM\n- From the Supervisor Dashboard, navigate to the Hierarchy List View (often accessed via a left-side icon) to see RMs reporting to you. The system can navigate to a Team Dashboard by default, and you can switch to the Hierarchy List View to drill into a specific RM’s individual dashboard. This establishes the per-RM drill-down path from team-level to individual performance. [2]\n\n3) Open the RM Dashboard for the selected RM\n- In the RM Dashboard (Team Dashboard path), you’ll access the individual RM’s performance metrics and portfolio view. This RM-specific dashboard is the authoritative source for the RM’s performance across leads, conversions, revenue, and activity. [2]\n\n4) Explore performance widgets and apply detailed filters\n- Within the RM dashboard, look for performance widgets such as revenue-range by number of customers and related drill-down capabilities. For example, a RM can view a Revenue Range by Number of Customers widget, with filters including:\n  • No. of Customers – filters all customers mapped to the RM\n  • No. of Customers with Investment Products – filters customers with investments\n  • No. of Customers with Deposit Products – filters deposit customers\n- These widgets typically offer a Three Dots or similar action to drill into Level-3 details for deeper inspection. This enables viewing per-customer or per-segment detail tied to the RM’s performance. [3]\n\n5) Data sources feeding RM performance metrics\n- The RM performance view draws from leads and their statuses (e.g., total leads, client accepted/rejected, in progress, follow-up, new) at the RM level, as seen in Lead/Status figures within the Lead Summary and RM dashboards. In addition, revenue and activity data are surfaced in RM-specific widgets (e.g., revenue-based breakdowns, customer activity) to provide a complete performance picture. [1][3]\n\n6) Security and access considerations for supervisor visibility\n- Access to RM dashboards and supervisor views typically requires a secure login and navigation to an RM Office or supervisor-specific entry point, ensuring that supervisors can view only permitted data (e.g., supervisor dashboards, RM-level dashboards) and that non-wealth or restricted data is excluded as appropriate. This access control is explicitly described in supervisor-dashboard journeys, including login steps and office-based navigation. [4]\n\nPutting it together (typical path): Lead Summary (supervisor view) → Hierarchy List View/Team Dashboard → select RM → RM Dashboard → use RM performance widgets with time/region/RM filters → drill into Level-3 details as needed. [1][2][3][4]\n\nSources\n- JioBlackRock_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V11_CCV_V10.pdf\n- HSBC_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - Supervisor Dashboard _V11_CCV_V10.pdf\n- JioBlackRock_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V10_CCV10.pdf\n- SBI_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V10_CCV13.pdf', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["RM","INVESTOR","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","Mutual Funds","Flow Diagram","Minimum Amount/Unit Validation","Systematic Running Status Report"],"seed_node_ids":["system:rmws","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:investor","report:systematic_running_s