lection criteria\\n\\nReport Selection Criteria \\n(This will appear as input fields\\nfor generating the report)\\n\\n Alert Date (Period)\\nClient (searchable field by name, ID or CIF)\\nCustomer Segment\\nSales Staff (this is for supervisor only and all the sales staff who reports the \\n\\nlogged in user will display in the drop-down field)\\nReport Sorting Sequence By default, records are grouped and sorted by sales staff name (ascending), \\n\\nCustomer name (ascending), date (ascending)\\nReport Page Break 50\\nDistribution Report can be exported in excel format\\nReport Frequency Ad hoc (as and when downloaded)\\nReport Ad Hoc Request Yes\\nReport Format Excel\\nCountry / Entity MY,SG, TH\\nAccess Access to report subject to user access matrix\\nRemarks Date Stamp (of as at when report is downloaded) should be stated\\n\\nField Description...","query":"customer risk rating product risk rating","norm_score":0.9131172080276487,"relevance_score":0.5156974065942869},{"filename":"Journey of Assessing Risk_Base_V1.0.pdf","file_id":"file-TJwTyfAdSu7L2mQckDVVMt","score":0.7450813870461775,"text":"Internal to HSBC and Intellect  Page 5 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n   \\n \\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n4. Process Flow \\n\\n4.1. Login \\n\\n1. The User enters their credentials and logs into the application \\n \\n\\n \\nScreen: Launch the application \\n\\n \\n\\n2. Once logged in, they can click on “Operation Office” to set up the risk profiling-related maintenance or “PMS” to  do \\nthe risk profiling for the customers \\n\\n \\n\\nInternal to HSBC and Intellect  Page 6 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n   \\n \\n\\n \\nScreen: Select Operation Office \\n\\n4.2. Questionnaire \\n\\n \\n\\nA risk profile Questionnaire is maintained in the system to evaluate the customer’s willingness and ability to take risks. It is \\n\\nneeded to compute the risk score and the acceptable level of risk that the customer is prepared and able to accept \\n\\n1. The User clicks on the “Operation Office” icon on the 