 from the previous discussion.\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what is the diffrence between CRR and PRRR process workflow steps","norm_score":0.817528286360198,"relevance_score":0.47384445579103207},{"filename":"WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF  V1.0_SBI_CCV1.3.pdf","file_id":"file-TMMZJ9hfChbHUJMwwK3zbC","score":0.7273539736127997,"text":"7. If the RMWS does the order journey and the Product Risk Profile is only  2 level up than the Customer Risk \\nProfile  (PRR=CRR+2) ,then the system will throw a warning displayed to the RMWS prompting him to \\nconfirm the same. All the securities where there is a mismatch would be shown in the pop-up \\nmessage.(applicable for Purchase and Switch transaction type). Through the client portal this deviation \\nwill be hard Stop.Customer would not be able to place order. \\n\\n8. In the above scenario when the RM will submit the order for authorization then the Order will go first to \\nCircle head/ Zonal head for approval and after they have approved the order will go for further \\nauthorization to RMWS. \\n\\n9. If in 