ct staff''s recommendation later and apply for FX Margin \\nTrading account on his/her own accord without advisory.\\n\\niii. However, if customer selects \\"More than 3\\" for Question 5f(i):, customer will \\nFAIL CKA, customer is unable to purchase products on his/her own accord and \\nadvisory MUST be provided by staff.\\n\\n4. E-learning- SD/ DCI: \\n\\na.  Date Passed\\n\\nb.  1st Attempt\\n\\nc.  Number of attempts\\n\\nd. Results\\n\\nIf this box is checked, customer has a conditional pass for the CKA:\\n\\ni. Uploading of certificate is required. \\n\\nii. Customer may reject staff''s recommendation later and purchase SD/DCI on \\nhis/her own accord without advisory.\\n\\niii. However, if customer selects \\"More than 3\\" for Question 5f(i):, customer will \\nFAIL CKA, customer is unable to purchase products on his/her own accord and \\nadvisory MUST be provided by staff.\\n\\n5. E-learning- Contracts for Difference: \\n\\na.  Date Passed\\n\\nb.  1st Attempt\\n\\nc.  Number of attempts\\n\\nd. Results\\n\\nIf this box is checked, customer has a conditional pass for the CKA:\\n\\ni. Uploading of certificate is required. \\n\\nii. Customer may reject staff''s recommendation later but CIMB Bank does not have\\nContracts for Difference available for customer''s own purchase without advisory.\\n\\niii. AND if customer selects \\"More than 3\\" for Question 5f(i):, customer will FAIL \\nCKA, customer is unable to purchase products on his/her own accord and advisory \\nMUST be provided by staff.\\n\\n6. Question: Have you been refused from transacting in the unlisted Specified \\nInvestment Product by another Financial Institution?\\n\\nIf yes is selected, to open up following questions:\\n\\n7. Question 5f(i): No. of times refused\\n\\nIf \\"More than 3\\" is selected: \\n\\n1. It means customer fails CKA (despite questions V.1-V.5 being checked)\\n\\n       Confidential to CIMB and Intellect                                                                      