('36', '11', 'assistant', '# **KG + VectorStore Answer - [Focused Response Directive]\n\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\n\nUser''s Question: Why is OTP used in wealth management transactions?**\n\n_Generated: 2025-10-23 18:25_\n\n## **Answer**\n\n**Direct Answer:** OTP is used as a second-factor authentication for wealth management transactions. SEBI mandates 2FA for outflow transactions like redemptions, switches, STP, and SWP, with OTP sent to verified channels before order placement. Regulatory updates extend 2FA to inflows, including new subscriptions and SIPs. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n**Key Points:**\n• Point 1: OTP enables 2FA for outflow transactions (redemption, switch, SWP, STP). <sup><a href="#cite-2">[2]</a></sup> [KG:compliance:two_factor_authentication]  \n• Point 2: 2FA also applies to inflows, including purchases and SIPs. <sup><a href="#cite-2">[2]</a></sup> [KG:compliance:two_factor_authentication]  \n• Point 3: OTPs are delivered to the folio-registered mobile or email before processing. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG:dataentity:otp]\n\n**Note:** This aligns with SEBI 2FA requirements for transaction authentication. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n---\n\n## **Citations**\n\n<a id="cite-1"></a>\n**[1]** → **WQ-Observation Solutioning_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.6.docx.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-2"></a>\n**[2]** → **WQ_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding -DIY - V.1.0.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-3"></a>\n**[3]** → **WQ_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding -DIY - V.1.0.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-4"></a>\n**[4]** → **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_MF_Client Porta...**\n\n<a id="cite-5"></a>\n**[5]** → **WQ-Observation Solutioning( 27 Jan-Apr release)_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.0...**\n\n<a id="cite-6"></a>\n**[6]** → **WQ-Observation Solutioning( 27 Jan-Apr release)_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.0...**\n\n\n---\n\n## **Sources by File**\n\n- **WQ-Observation Solutioning( 27 Jan-Apr release)_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.0...** → [5], [6]\n- **WQ-Observation Solutioning_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.6.docx.pdf** → [1]\n- **WQ_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding -DIY - V.1.0.pdf** → [2], [3]\n- **WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_MF_Client Porta...** → [4]\n', '992515a8-4039-4c37-a376-eda8f55dc2b9', '[{"filename":"WQ-Observation Solutioning_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.6.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-DApMRsCEwmyK4e4XhZnwY9","score":0.8613900550552933,"text":"3.17. Observation 32,34 \\n\\n3.17.1. Description \\n\\nEffective from 1st June 2022, SEBI has introduced Two factor authentication for all outflow transactions like Redemptions, Switches, \\nSystematic transfer plan (STP), Systematic withdrawal plan (SWP). It is now mandatory to use 2FA. Hence, before placing the order \\nfrom IWMS, 2FA should be done on the email or Mobile no or both of the Investor which is registered in the Folio which is being \\noutflowed. The same information needs to be sent to RTA as a part of 168 common feed file formats when the transaction is \\nprocessed. Below are the Major requirements for the implementation of the norm led by SEBI.  \\n\\n● Client information like email and mobile no, Transaction mode selected by RMWS while placing the order should be sent \\nin feed file.  \\n\\n● Upload and Download Validations for transaction slips  \\n● Removal of Multiple outflow orders from order journey and Removal of Simultaneous placement of Inflow and outflow \\n\\norders in Order journey (Client Portal) \\n● File upload to be provided for Investor Master Report (KFintech-MSD211 and CAMS WBR-9 (Folio master feed file solution \\n\\nto be considered also) \\n● MIS Report download (Format Attached) \\n\\nThis section covers the changes done due to the below observations raised by Bank: \\n\\nObservation 32: Upload of WBR9 and MFSD211 to store mobile and email no of RTA.Second factor authentication \\nchanges in order journey. \\nObservation 34: INB integration - OTP services should be changed from INB services to ARX services. \\nOTP should  be sent to Mobile number stored in  folio master (WBR9 and MFSD211)  for Redemption, Switchout, SWP and STP and \\n\\nInternal to SBI and Intellect  Page 75 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                                                                          \\n\\nfor Subscriptions and SIP to the mobile number stored in customer profile (as received from CBS). \\n\\n3.17.2. PSL Reference \\n\\n WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_MF_Client Portal_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.1 \\n\\n  WQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF  V1.0_SBI_CCV1. \\n\\n \\n\\n3.17.3. Business Rules \\n\\n1. System is storing investor master report which is as per RTA and the same will be used for folio level details (Refer \\nKFintech-MSD211, MFSD 246-211and CAMS WBR-9) \\n\\n2. For transaction type Subscription and SIP,OTP will be sent to a mobile number  which is registered in the CBS. (Client \\nPortal only) \\n","query":"two factor authentication folio","norm_score":1,"relevance_score":0.6386147003902775},{"filename":"WQ_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding -DIY - V.1.0.pdf","file_id":"file-PGVRKSb8kGQfwUk1wVcgZc","score":0.8032097611397195,"text":"Not \\nApplicable\\n\\n12\\n\\nNominee \\nGuardian \\nName\\n\\nNeed to \\nenter the \\nnominee \\nguardian \\nname Input Yes String Optional\\n\\nNot \\nApplicable\\n\\nRequired in case of \\nminor\\n\\nE-Sign\\n\\n1\\nVID/\\nAadhaar\\n\\nNeed to \\nenter the \\nVirtual ID or\\nAadhaar Id Input Yes Numeric Yes\\n\\nNot \\nApplicable\\n\\n2 Enter OTP\\n\\nNeed to \\nenter the \\nOTP Input Yes Numeric Yes\\n\\nNot \\nA