nEffective from 1st April 2023, SEBI has introduced two factor authentications for all Inflow transactions as well (Subscription, \\nAdditional Subscription, Fresh SIP, and Additional SIP). It is now mandatory to use 2FA. Hence, before placing the order from IWMS, \\n2FA should be done on the Mobile no of the Investor which is registered in the Folio which is being in flowed and Outflowed. The \\nsame information needs to be sent to RTA as a part of 168 common feed file formats when the transaction is processed. Below are \\nthe Major requirements for the implementation of the norm led by SEBI.  \\n\\n1. Client information like email and mobile no. Transaction mode selected by RMWS while placing the order should be sent \\nin the feed file.  \\n\\n2. Upload and Download Validations for transaction slips  \\n3. Removal of Multiple outflow orders from order journey and Removal of Simultaneous placement of Inflow and outflow \\n\\norders in Order journey (Client Portal) \\n4. Fetching information from Folio Master report \\n\\nInternal to SBI and Intellect  Page 14 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                                                                        \\n\\n1.2.2. PSL Reference \\n\\nWQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_MF_Client Portal_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.1 \\nWQ_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - MF V1.0_SBI_CCV1.3 \\nWQ-Observation Solutioning_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.6 \\n\\n1.2.3. Business Rules \\n\\n1. System is storing investor master report which is as per RTA and the same will be used for folio level details (Refer \\nKFintech-MSD211, MFSD 246-211and CAMS WBR-9) \\n\\n2. Inflow Transactions = Subscription, Additional Subscription, Additional SIP and SIP \\n3. Outflow Transactions = Redemption, SWP, STP and Switch \\n4. For t...","query":"two factor authentication folio","norm_score":0.4083178307370735,"relevance_score":0.46743067088208107},{"f