('38', '12', 'assistant', '# **KG + VectorStore Answer - [Focused Response Directive]\n\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\n\nUser''s Question: What''s the difference between buy and sell orders?**\n\n_Generated: 2025-10-28 06:26_\n\n## **Answer**\n\n**Direct Answer:** \n- Buy and sell are two distinct order types in the system. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n- The Order Management System processes both via initiation, routing, and validation flows. <sup><a href="#cite-2">[2]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n- The order data includes fields like Price, Quantity, and Time in Force. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n<sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n**Key Points:**\n• Point 1: The order type field explicitly includes Buy and Sell. <sup><a href="#cite-2">[2]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n• Point 2: Orders carry fields such as Price, Quantity, and Time in Force. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n• Point 3: Processing involves authorization and fund transfer steps. <sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n\n**Note:** The sources define order types; no behavioral differences between Buy and Sell are specified. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG: dataentity:order]\n\n---\n\n## **Citations**\n\n<a id="cite-1"></a>\n**[1]** → **UJ_2.1_Order placement.docx.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-2"></a>\n**[2]** → **Order Management System.docx.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-3"></a>\n**[3]** → **Order execution scenario-RM Office - automatic approach.docx.pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-4"></a>\n**[4]** → **WQ_Journey of Trade Proces