levance_score":0.6161349985029174},{"filename":"Order Management System.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-X9vVxhjYGX88SRp8grKwjS","score":0.7486931991615177,"text":"Process Area Process Sub Process Intellect Module Intellect Process Name \\n\\nOrder \\nManagement \\nSystem Order Flow   OMS Order Management \\n\\n \\n3. Process Flow Diagram: \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\nProcess ID_1.2a – Order Initiation \\n\\n \\n\\n15 | Page \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                \\n\\n \\n\\n \\nProcess ID_1.2b – Order Routing \\n\\n4. Description of process steps –  \\na. Process Description: \\n\\ni. Orders for Fixed Income/Equity/ETF/Structured Product instrument can be initiated by \\nRelationship Manager, ISD, AMD or Treasury. \\n\\nii. The investment request may come through mail, fax or call from investor. In case of DPM \\ncustomers and Proprietary Funds, AMD will initiate the orders. \\n\\niii. For NDPMS portfolios, system will check for Communication Indemnity document in case \\nMode of Instruction is Mail, Fax or Telephone. \\n\\niv. During Order capture process, the document submission status and document expiry date will \\nbe validated by OMS. List of Documents for FI/Equity is as follows: \\nDocument Expiry Date Validation: \\nW8 Ben \\nFATCA \\nLeverage \\nPassport \\nEmirates ID \\nPOA \\n \\nDocument Submission Status: \\nLeverage Agreement - Leverage Orders \\nRisk Profile Document \\n\\n16 | Page \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                \\n\\nW8 Ben - Equity \\nFATCA - Equity \\nLeverage - Leverage Orders \\nPassport \\nEmirates ID \\nPOA \\n\\nv. After document validations, OMS will validate other pre-trade validations as mentioned below: \\n● Customer Trade Multiple validation \\n● Minimum Customer lot size validation \\n● Security Trade Multiple validation \\n● NCMV being negative validation \\n● Market status (open/close) validation \\n● On selection of ''Time in force'' checks for limit order and shows error if Good till day is \\n\\nselected for limit order \\n● If Valid till Date is less than Business Date, error message shown \\n\\nvi. For Equity/ETF orders of NDPM investors, OMS will default the trading account meant for \\nEquity transactions. For Bonds, if there is only cash account then that will be default populated \\nelse user will have to select. System will fetch the cash balance available for the Core Bank \\naccount by making a call to Core Bank. Core Bank will also send information such whether \\nDr/Cr is allowed in the cash/trading account or not. Depending on this flag OMS will allow the \\ntransaction to proceed. \\n\\nvii. In case of Limit Order, OMS will allow u...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What''s the difference between buy and sell orders? process workflow steps","norm_score":0.8740784088367413,"relevance_score":0.5102702905751001},{"filename":"Order execution scenario-RM Office - automatic approach.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-5XcWm8SuhJnKiUj78csxY4","score":0.7147195455375095,"text":"3.9. On confirmation of the order, system will generate the unique order number and the status of the order will \\n\\nbe updated to “Pending”. \\n\\n7 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n3.10. User will select the order under “Oder(s) in Pending State” and click on “Submit. \\n\\n3.11. The order will now flow for authorization. \\n\\n3.12. The authorizer will log into the application. \\n\\n3.13. The authorizer will click on “Supervisor Approval”. \\n\\n \\n\\n3.14. In “Supervisor Approval” screen, user will select “Order Authorization” under Authorize menu. \\n\\n3.15. All the orders that are currently available for pending are displayed under “Pending Approval Listing” \\n\\n3.16. The authorizer will navigate to the desired order and click on “Claim”. \\n\\n8 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n3.17. Upon being claimed, the order will move to “To Approve” list. \\n\\n3.18. In “To Approve” list, user will navigate to the desired order and review the details. \\n\\n3.19. The authorizer will then click on “Authorize” to authorize the order. \\n\\n3.20. To reject, the authorizer will click on “Reject”, system will prompt the authorizer to enter a reject reason. \\n\\n3.21. The authorizer can click on “Release” to release the order back in “Pending Approval Listing”. \\n\\n \\n\\n3.22. Upon authorization, system will call the “Fund Transfer API”. \\n\\n3.23. The order amount will be debited from the customer’s settlement account through “Fund Transfer API”. \\n\\n3.24. The Fund Transfer API will be considered successful if “Response Status” is 0 (Success) and journal \\n\\nnumber is generated. \\n\\n3.25. If the Response Status is 0 (Successes), but the journal number in the response is null, then it will be \\n\\nconsidered as failure. \\n9 \\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n3.26. If in the response of Fund Transfer API, ResponseStatus is “1” and error code is received, then it will be \\n\\nconsidered as failure.   There are 2 kinds of failures.  (i) Genuine rejection by the Bank like insufficient fund \\n\\nand (ii) Technical error for which the fund transfer should be tried again after enquiry.  \\n\\n3.27. The following error codes will be considered as genuine rejection by bank and hence the subscription \\n\\ntransactions will be rejected and order status will be updated as “Failed”, after receiving response from \\n\\nbank. \\n\\n3.28. User will not be allowed to resubmit the order. He/She has to start from the transact screen again. \\n\\n \\n\\nNo retrigger for the following Error codes \\n\\nError Code Error Description \\n\\n0110 ACCOUNT CLOSED \\n\\n0112 ACCOUNT IS LOCKED - PLS. TRY AGAIN \\n\\n0113 ACCOUNT STOPPED \\n\\n2817 CANNOT PROCESS THE ACCOUNT-INOPERAT...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What''s the difference between buy and sell orders?","norm_score":0.7595159817800499,"relevance_score":0.49996529481305574},{"filename":"WQ_Journey of Trade Processing_V1.0_SBI_CCV1.2.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-EDHJujLK8QGVU8GhJkiXNe","score":0.7232393552515733,"text":"Internal to Client and Intellect                                                                                                                                               Page 16 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n      \\n \\n\\n# \\nTD_TRTYPE \\n(Karvy) Description (Karvy) \\n\\nTrnMode \\n(Karvy) \\n\\nTransaction Type \\n(Wealth) \\n\\nTransaction Mode \\n(Wealth) \\n\\nOrder and Transaction \\nto be Processed? \\n\\n73 SWINR Swit. Over In Rej. R Switch In Reversal T \\n\\n74 SWOF Switch Over Out N Switch Out Normal T \\n\\n75 SWOFR Swit. Over Out Rej. R Switch Out Reversal T \\n\\n76 SWOP Switch Over Out N Switch Out Normal T \\n\\n77 SWOPR Swit. Over Out Rej. R Switch Out Reversal T \\n\\n78 TRFI Demat Transfer In N NA NA NA \\n\\n79 TRFIR Demat Transfer in Rej R NA NA NA \\n\\n80 TRFO Demat Transfer Out N NA NA NA \\n\\n81 TRFOR Demat Transfer Out Rej R NA NA NA \\n\\n82 TRMI Transmission In N NA NA NA \\n\\n83 TRMO Transmission Out N NA NA NA \\n\\n84 UPLO Unpledging N NA NA NA \\n\\n85 UPLOR Unpledging Rejection R NA NA NA \\n \\n\\n4.2.1. FIFO Design and Lot Linkage (This is will be part of Order to trade matching event) \\n \\n\\nThe first in, first out (FIFO) method means that when units are sold, you must sell the first ones that you acquired first when \\n\\ncalculating gains and losses. On any day, transactions will be processed by the system in the below order \\n\\ni. Reversal – Out Transactions \\nii. Reversal – In Transaction \\n\\niii. Normal – In Transactions \\niv. Normal – Out Transactions \\n\\n \\n\\nNormal Transactions \\n\\n \\n\\n1. For every “Out” transaction, system will maintain the details of the transaction from which the units have been sold \\n2. For every “In” transaction, system will maintain the details of units remaining and units which have been sold \\n\\n \\n\\nThe below examples illustrates the above two points \\n\\n \\n\\nA. Customer made a subscription transaction for 100 units on 01-Jan-2021 for scheme 1 using folio 1, the below \\ninformation will be displayed as on 01-Jan-21 \\n\\n \\n\\nTransaction \\nNumber \\n\\nTransaction \\nDate \\n\\nTransaction \\nType \\n\\nTransaction \\nMode \\n\\nUnits User \\nTransaction \\nNumber \\n\\nUnits Remaining \\nin the Lot \\n\\nLot Linked \\n\\nA001 01-Jan-21 Subscription Normal 100 W001 100  \\n \\n\\nB. Customer made another subscription transaction for 50 units on 02-Jan-2021 for scheme 1 using folio 1, the below \\ninformation will be displayed as on 02-Jan-21 \\n \\n\\nTransaction \\nNumber \\n\\nTransaction \\nDate \\n\\nTransaction \\nType \\n\\nTransaction \\nMode \\n\\nUnits User \\nTransaction \\n\\nUnits Remaining \\nin the Lot \\n\\nLot Linked \\n\\nInternal to Client and Intellect...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What''s the difference between buy and sell orders? requirements rules conditions","norm_score":0.7882455994333771,"relevance_score":0.4908946154052314},{"filename":"Order execution scenario-RM Office - automatic approach.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-5XcWm8SuhJnKiUj78csxY4","score":0.7028331394102324,"text":"3.25. If the Response Status is 0 (Successes), but the journal number in the response is null, then it will be \\n\\nconsidered as failure. \\n9 \\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n3.26. If in the response of Fund Transfer API, ResponseStatus is “1” and error code is received, then it will be \\n\\nconsidered as failure.   There are 2 kinds of failures.  (i) Genuine rejection by the Bank like insufficient fund \\n\\nand (ii) Technical error for which the fund transfer should be tried again after enquiry.  \\n\\n3.27. The following error codes will be considered as genuine rejection by bank and hence the subscription \\n\\ntransactions will be rejected and order status will be updated as “Failed”, after receiving response from \\n\\nbank. \\n\\n3.28. User will not be allowed to resubmit the order. He/She has to start from the transact screen again. \\n\\n \\n\\nNo retrigger for the following Error codes \\n\\nError Code Error Description \\n\\n0110 ACCOUNT CLOSED \\n\\n0112 ACCOUNT IS LOCKED - PLS. TRY AGAIN \\n\\n0113 ACCOUNT STOPPED \\n\\n2817 CANNOT PROCESS THE ACCOUNT-INOPERATIVE \\n\\n0398 INSUFFICIENT FUNDS \\n \\n\\n3.29. If the “Fund Transfer API” has failed due to a technical reason, the status of the order will be updated as \\n\\n“In Progress”.  The following error codes will be considered as technical reasons. \\n\\nRe-triggered for the following Error codes (Technical reasons) \\n\\nError Code Error Description \\n\\n6970 DP NOT AVAILABLE. ACCT CANNOT BE OVERDRAWN \\n\\nSI001 EXCEPTION WHILE PROCESSING THE RESPONSE \\n\\nSI002 ERROR IN CONNECTING DESTINATION SERVER \\n\\n0155 PL CONTACT SERVICE DESK     INVM   X04T  \\n\\n2066 SWEEP DETAILS NOT FOUND \\n\\nSI014 TIMEOUT PLEASE TRY AFTER SOMETIME \\n\\nSI011  INPUT STRING/REQUEST WAS NOT IN CORRECT FORMAT \\n\\n0545 APPLICATION NOT ACTIVE. \\n\\n7527 CIF not scrutinized by LCPC \\n\\n8123 WITHDRAWAL/TRANSFER STOPPED KYC UPDATION OVERDUE IN ACCOUNT \\n\\nSI094  INVALID REQUEST REFERENCE NUMBER \\n\\nSI163 JOURNAL/REFERENCE NUMBER MISMATCH \\n\\nSI007 Unable to process due to technical error \\n \\n\\n3.30. On success, the order will be then sent to RTA through RTA API and the status of the order will be \\n\\nupdated as “Authorized” in order book. \\n\\n \\n\\n3.31. If “RTA API” fails, then the order will remain in “Authorized” state. \\n\\n3.32. The status of the order can be accessed from Order Book. \\n\\n3.33. On every 30 mins, system will again execute all the orders that are currently in “In Progress” state till the \\n\\ncut-off time. \\n\\n3.34. At the time of execution, system will first call the “Fund Transfer Enquiry API” to check if the amount has \\n\\nbeen debited from the cust...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What''s the difference between buy and sell orders?","norm_score":0.7194338772765739,"relevance_score":0.45172119141512},{"filename":"UJ_3.4.3_Customer Response.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-8RxfKwnrRfsWttfnAmKavF","score":0.6269812913240213,"text":"UJ_3.4.3_Customer Response.docx\\n\\n\\n       \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\nUser Journey Document \\n\\n \\n \\n\\n \\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n \\n\\nConfidential to Customer and Intellect Page 1 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n       \\n\\nCONTENTS \\nUSER JOURNEY_3.4.3 – CUSTOMER RESPONSE 3 \\n\\n \\n\\n●  \\n\\nConfidential to Customer and Intellect Page 2 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n       \\n\\nUser Journey_3.4.3 – Customer Response \\n\\n1. Process Objective –  \\nThe objective of this process is to capture investor’s responses for a voluntary corporate action (i.e. for \\na Corporate Action which requires Customer Response Capture, it could Corporate Action like Voting \\nRights or Conversion). \\n \\n \\n\\n2. Event Definition Process flow Map \\n \\n \\n\\nProcess \\nArea \\n\\nProcess Sub Process Intellect Module Intellect Process Name \\n\\nCorporate \\nActions \\n\\nCustomer \\nResponse \\n\\n \\nIntellect Portfolio \\n\\nManagement \\nExchange \\n\\nCorporate Action –Customer \\nResponse - \\n\\n \\n \\n \\n\\n \\n \\n\\n3. Description of process steps –  \\n\\nProcess Description \\n● This process is applicable only for voluntary corporate actions. Customer response is \\n\\nentered after entitlement calculation on record date.  \\n● The process will need to be completed on or before the customer response date.  \\n● In case of corporate action like Voting Rights, user will have provision to capture the \\n\\nresolutions and customer response for each resolution.  \\n \\n\\nConfidential to Customer and Intellect Page 3 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n       \\n\\n● User can capture the customer response at individual record level and save it. Once \\nresponse for all the customers is captured user can submit the same \\n\\n● The settlement process will depend on the customer response \\n● Customer details and the CA specific details are populated automatically in the customer \\n\\nresponse window. \\n● The user can Modify the Customer response if required \\n● The saved record moves to Checker''s grid for Authorization \\n● The Checker has a provision to view the Event details and the Customer level benefits , \\n\\nreview it and Authorize or Reject  in case of any discrepancies \\n● If rejected, the record moves to the maker for modification and re processing \\n● Authorized customer response records moves for Settlement Process. \\n● Application would fetch all investors who have holdings in the security and for whom \\n\\nresponse needs to be captured. \\n\\n. \\n\\n \\n4. Input details – Displayed \\n\\n \\n5. Validations \\n\\n● The event should be a voluntary corporate action. \\n● Entitlement calculation should have been authorized. \\n\\n \\n\\nException Management \\n● Mandatory Field Verification \\n\\n●.i.2.●.i. System will valid...","query":"[focused response directive] please","norm_score":0.46365415132590376,"relevance_score":0.3777460963855286}]', '{"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_689b49252a4c8191a12a1528a475fbd8","response_id":"79d659c8-1f78-418c-94c7-65706dddecee","is_conversational":false,"mode":"concise","processing_time_seconds":94.48,"request_id":"6997805f-97d3-47c9-9ce5-6ff271bcde41"}', '2025-10-28 06:26:45.460172'),
