('48', '18', 'assistant', '# **KG + VectorStore Answer - [Focused Response Directive]\n\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\n\nUser''s Question: How are customer accounts categorized?**\n\n_Generated: 2025-10-31 06:43_\n\n## **Answer**\n\n**Direct Answer:** Customer accounts are categorized by product ownership, client type, and product category. First, all customers are divided into two buckets based on whether they hold the product in their holdings or not. Second, all customers with client type ''Primary'' are further bucketed by product ownership. Third, opportunity by product category groups customers by holdings for each category. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n**Key Points:**\n• Point 1: Two buckets based on holdings of the product (active accounts). <sup><a href="#cite-2">[2]</a></sup> [KG:dataentity:active_accounts]\n• Point 2: All customers with client type ''Primary'' are divided into two buckets by product ownership. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup> [KG:dataentity:investor]\n• Point 3: Opportunity by Product Category splits into two buckets by holdings for each category. <sup><a href="#cite-3">[3]</a></sup> [KG:dataentity:mutual_funds]\n\n**Note:** These categorizations reflect the SBI journey framework described in the source. <sup><a href="#cite-1">[1]</a></sup>\n\n---\n\n## **Citations**\n\n<a id="cite-1"></a>\n**[1]** → **WQ_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V1.0_SBI_CCV.1.3.doc...**\n\n<a id="cite-2"></a>\n**[2]** → **CBC_OperatingManual_Ver1.0..pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-3"></a>\n**[3]** → **WQ_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V1.0_SBI_CCV.1.3.doc...**\n\n<a id="cite-4"></a>\n**[4]** → **CBC_OperatingManual_Ver1.0..pdf**\n\n<a id="cite-5"></a>\n**[5]** → **CBC_OperatingManual_Ver1.0..pdf**\n\n\n---\n\n## **Sources by File**\n\n- **CBC_OperatingManual_Ver1.0..pdf** → [2], [4], [5]\n- **WQ_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V1.0_SBI_CCV.1.3.doc...** → [1], [3]\n', '4d8a767b-68e8-4d8d-9a65-2da9734d1fc5', '[{"filename":"WQ_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V1.0_SBI_CCV.1.3.docx.pdf","file_id":"file-CSeBsxH4YA9aU5C5Fmowzc","score":0.8259207756172463,"text":"client type as “Primary”. \\nInsurance is included for customers with \\n\\nclient type as “Primary”. \\n\\nCustomer details (by AUM \\nChange Range) – Level 3 \\n\\nAll investment accounts are included. \\nCASA/FD is included \\nInsurance is included \\n\\nAll investment accounts are included for \\ncustomers with client type as “Primary”. \\nCASA/FD is included for customers with \\n\\nclient type as “Primary”. \\nInsurance is included for customers with \\n\\nclient type as “Primary”. \\n\\nNet New Money – Level 2 \\nAll new investment accounts opened are \\n\\ncounted. \\nCASA/FD is excluded \\n\\nAll new investment accounts opened for \\ncustomers with client type as “Primary”. \\nCASA/FD is included for customers with \\n\\nclient type as “Primary” \\n\\nCustomer Details (Net New \\nMoney) Range – Level 3 \\n\\nAll new investment accounts opened are \\ncounted. \\n\\nCASA/FD is excluded \\n\\nAll new investment accounts opened for \\ncustomers with client type as “Primary”. \\nCASA/FD is included for customers with \\n\\nclient type as “Primary”. \\n\\nInternal to SBI and Intellect         Page 70 \\n \\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                                                                         \\n\\n \\n\\nOpportunity Summary – \\nLevel 1 \\n\\nAll customers are divided into 2 buckets \\n1. Number of customers who have the \\n\\nproduct in their holdings \\n2. Number of customers who does not \\n\\nhave the product in their holdings \\n\\nAll customers with client type as \\n“Primary” are divided into 2 buckets \\n\\n1. Number of customers who have the \\nproduct in their holdings \\n\\n2. Number of customers who does not \\nhave the product in their holdings \\n\\nOpportunity by Product \\nCategory – Level 2 \\n\\nAll customers are divided into 2 buckets \\n1. Number of customers who have \\n\\nholdings for a product category \\n2. Number of customers who does not \\nhave holdings for a product category \\n\\nAll customers with client type as \\n“Primary” are divided into 2 buckets \\n1. Number of customers who have \\n\\nholdings for a product category \\n2. Number of customers who does not \\nhave holdings for a product category \\n\\nCustomer Details (by \\nProduct Category) – Level \\n\\n3 \\n\\nAll customers are divided into 2 buckets \\n1. Number of customers who have \\n\\nholdings for a product category \\n2. Number of customers who does not \\nhave holdings for a product category \\n\\nAll customers with client type as \\n“Primary” are divided into 2 buckets \\n1. Number of customers who have \\n\\nholdings for a product category \\n2. Number of customers w...","query":"[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How are customer accounts categorized?","norm_score":0.9083052537560725,"relevance_score":0.6095940188479732},{"filename":"CBC_OperatingManual_Ver1.0..pdf","file_id":"file-FPxbZhNkP4LGiaw8XJqghm","score":0.8328910616974694,"text":"g. Branch gets the account opening forms filled up by the customer  and submits these to Trust Group\\nfor validation\\n\\nh. Trust Group approves the docs and sends it back to the branch\\n\\ni. Agreement is created (signed by both Customer n Trust Group)\\n\\nj. Upon creation of agreement, TSA account opening  is requested by the Trust Group to Core Bank (HQ\\nMain Branch, Makati) via a Memo\\n\\nk. Upon TSA account opening in core bank, product subscription and activation is initiated in Intellect\\nsystem\\n\\nl. When a customer wants to invest in a product they need to subscribe to it  which is done during\\nProduct  Subscription.  Client  specific  details  are  captured  like  Agreement  No.,  Mandate,  Related\\nParties, Client Preferences etc are captured during subscription \\n\\nm. In Product Activation, linking of Accounts to the portfolio is done so that the investments can be\\nactivated. Both, Internal  (Security/ Investment  Account) and External (TSA/ CSA) accounts can be\\nlinked\\n\\nn. In this arrangement, member register would be maintained in Trust Banking system\\n\\n4. Lifecycle (Movement of Money)\\n\\nContribution of Funds\\na. Cash is deposited in the employee benefit fund via Contribution Upload\\n\\nb. Contribution to the fund are made periodically (Once in every 15 days for Provident Fund)and form\\npart of the fund\\n\\nc. All the fund processing would happen through the TSA (Trust Savings Account)\\n\\nd. Contribution Upload File is attached below\\n\\nWithdrawal of Funds\\na. CBC  will  make  payments  only  upon  receipt  of  specific  written  instructions  from  the  authorized\\n\\nrepresentative of the client\\n\\nInternal – CBC Operating Manual Page 7\\n\\n\\n\\n                                                                                                                                                                                         \\nb. Cash is withdrawn via Employee Withdrawal transaction and Benefits (Final Withdrawal Amount) will\\n\\nbe computed by the system\\n\\nc. Wi