('202', '81', 'assistant', 'Bulk transfer of client ownership across agents is supported through delegated handover functionality in the Operations Office. The feature enables an Operations User Maker to temporarily or permanently reassign leads, prospects, and customers from one relationship manager (RM) to another, with specific UI paths and safeguards in place.\n\nKey concepts and capabilities\n- Delegation and handover foundations: Delegation allows temporary reassignment of leads, prospects, and customers between RMs under the same Operations User Maker, typically used when a RM is unavailable, with auto-authorization in some configurations. This supports bulk reassignment workflows when a large group of clients needs to move to a new agent in one action or within a single delegation session [1].\n- Distinct delegation modes: The system exposes tabs for Lead Delegation, Prospect Delegation, and Client Delegation to organize bulk moves by client type, helping users apply the transfer to a broad set of records in a controlled manner [1]. In contrast, handover is designed for permanent reassignment (e.g., a RM exiting or a client-initiated change of RM) and is performed via a dedicated handover path in the Relationship area, with similar bulk-selection capabilities [2].\n\nHow to perform a bulk transfer (high-level steps)\n1) Access path and scope\n- Open the Operations/Relationship area and navigate to Delegation (for temporary reassignment) or Handover (for permanent reassignment) depending on the business need. This path is the standard entry point for bulk ownership changes and is documented as the main UI for bulk client transfers [1][2].\n\n2) Define source and destination\n- In the Delegation/Handover screen, specify the source agent (current RM) and the destination agent (new RM). The transfer operates within the governance boundaries of the Operations User Maker role [1].\n\n3) Bulk selection or filtering\n- Use the provided filters to identify the eligible client set (e.g., by status, ownership, product holdings, or other criteria). The UI supports selecting multiple clients and reflecting them in a Selected Clients List for bulk processing [2].\n- After filtering, you can review the Selected Clients List to confirm the bulk set before applying the transfer [2].\n\n4) Execute the bulk transfer\n- Confirm the transfer action. Delegation can be auto-authorized in some configurations, enabling a seamless bulk move without per-client approvals, while handover may require explicit action for permanent reassignment [1].\n\n5) Audit and traceability\n- Every delegation or handover action is captured in an audit trail. You can view the audit entries and download them (e.g., as XLS) to satisfy governance and regulatory requirements [3]. Additional audit trail documentation highlights IDs, timestamps, and the ability to export logs for review [4].\n\n6) Data integrity and regulatory constraints\n- Transfers are governed by permissions/entitlements, ensuring only authorized users can perform bulk reassignments. Delegation is designed to maintain a clear ownership lineage under the controlling Operations User Maker, with scope limited to the appropriate relationship group (e.g., RM within the same operational hierarchy) [1].\n- For permanent reassignment (handover), the process is intended to reflect a lasting change of ownership, and it is documented to support scenarios like RM exits or client-requested changes, reinforcing data integrity and accountability [2].\n- Audit trails provide the necessary evidence and accountability for transfers, enabling downstream reconciliation and regulatory reporting [3].\n\nPractical implications and best practices\n- Use bulk delegation for temporary coverage or large-scale reassignment when the business need is time-bound, leveraging the automated/auto-authorized flow where permitted to reduce manual steps [1].\n- Prefer handover for permanent ownership changes to ensure a lasting, auditable record of the new owner and associated responsibilities [2].\n- Always validate the transfer through the audit trail post-action, and export or review the logs as part of governance and regulatory compliance activities [3].\n\nIn short, bulk client ownership transfer from one agent to another is supported via Delegation/Handover workflows, with UI paths to filter and bulk-select clients, controlled permissions, and comprehensive audit trails to ensure data integrity and regulatory compliance [1][2][3][4].\n\nSources\n- HSBC_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf [1]\n- JBR_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf [2]\n- Maybank_Audit Trail_V13_CCV12.pdf [3]\n- SBI_Audit Trail_V10.pdf [4]', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Pending Approval Listing","To Approve tab","Supervisor Approval screen","User Office","INVESTOR","RM","Order","customer","Product Cart","External Systems"],"seed_node_ids":["datastore:pending_approval_listing","system:user_office","system:rmws","report:performance_projection","datastore:product_cart","system:product_cart","system:to_approve_tab","dataentity:pending_approval_listing","dataentity:investor","dataentity:rm","dataentity:order","dataentity:product_cart","dataentity:customer","system:external_systems","report:product_cart","system:supervisor_approval_screen"],"expanded_nodes":52,"expanded_edges":83,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make 