('186', '78', 'assistant', '# Custom Report: Tracking Active Campaigns and Recording Customer Feedback\n\n## 1. Introduction\n\nTracking the progress of active campaigns and capturing customer feedback is crucial for strategic decision-making. This process involves monitoring campaign lifecycles, analyzing customer interactions, and ensuring compliance. This report outlines the features and methodologies used within financial platforms to achieve these goals, providing insights applicable to banks, consulting firms, and regulatory bodies.\n\n## 2. Tracking Active Campaign Progress\n\n### Campaign Management Module\n\nThe **Campaign Management** module is central to monitoring campaigns. It comprises several core components:\n\n- **Campaign Dashboard**: A comprehensive interface that displays key campaign metrics.\n- **Lifecycle Tracking**: Provides insights into each campaign’s progress through different stages.\n\n#### Key Campaign Record Fields\n\n1. **Type**: Differentiates campaigns, such as event-based versus ongoing.\n2. **Status**: Indicates the current stage—New, Active, Completed, or Rejected.\n3. **Timeline**: Includes Start Date and End Date, crucial for scheduling and execution.\n4. **Yield Period**: Measures effectiveness post-campaign, crucial for ROI analysis.\n\n#### Performance Metrics\n\nAs campaigns progress, the system updates key performance metrics:\n\n- **Conversion Rate**: Percentage of targeted leads responding positively, recalculated daily.\n\nThese metrics ensure a real-time understanding of campaign effectiveness, supporting strategic adjustments when necessary.\n\n## 3. Recording Customer Feedback\n\nFeedback collection is vital for understanding customer perspectives and improving future campaigns. This process is managed using a **Capture Response Screen**, which includes:\n\n### Structured Fields\n\n- **Lead Status**: Tracks progression (e.g., Ready for Follow-Up, In Progress).\n- **Sub-Status**: Provides further detail (e.g., Call Back, Uncontactable).\n\n### Unstructured Fields\n\n- **Free-Text Notes**: Capture qualitative data such as customer attitudes or objections.\n\n#### Surveys for In-Depth Feedback\n\nSurveys offer structured feedback opportunities:\n- **Custom Forms**: Collect detailed insights post-event or for product interest.\n- **Data Storage**: Tracks responses, IDs, and survey details.\n\nThese mechanisms ensure comprehensive feedback is incorporated into campaign evaluations.\n\n## 4. Dashboards and Management Oversight\n\nEffective oversight requires comprehensive dashboards tailored to different user roles.\n\n### For Relationship Managers (RMs)\n\n- **Campaign Dashboard**: Shows total leads, contact status, and detailed lead responses.\n- **Drill-Down Capabilities**: Allow RMs to update records or analyze feedback.\n\n### For Supervisors and Management\n\n- **Supervisor Dashboards**: Display aggregate data, highlighting lead distribution by RM and response status.\n- **Performance Comparisons**: Facilitates comparison across campaigns and RMs, identifying potential bottlenecks.\n\nThese tools support active management and ensure compliance with organizational objectives.\n\n## 5. Governance, Approvals, and Audit Trail\n\n### Compliance and Approval Process\n\n- **Maker–Checker Approval**: Ensures new or modified campaigns receive supervisory approval before activation.\n- **Audit Trails**: Record detailed histories of all actions and changes.\n\nThis framework promotes transparency and accountability, supporting internal reviews and regulatory compliance.\n\n## 6. Conclusion\n\nThe integration of these tools within a campaign management platform ensures that campaigns are tracked effectively and customer feedback is systematically captured. By supporting data-driven decision-making and compliance, organizations can enhance their strategic initiatives.\n\n## Sources & References\n\n1. **Journey of Suspect to Lead – Campaign Dashboard**: Provides detailed dashboard functionalities.\n2. **Campaign Management Enhancements – Timeline & Conversions**: Describes key metrics and performance indicators.\n3. **Client Portal Journey – Survey Feedback Capture**: Details survey execution and analysis.\n4. **Audit Trail – Campaign Approval & Logging**: Outlines compliance processes.\n\n## Limitations\n\nSome data points and processes are based on industry standards and may vary by platform and region. Continuous updates and regional adaptations should be considered for precise application.\n\nThis report provides a comprehensive framework suitable for stakeholders looking to optimize campaign tracking and customer feedback processes within their organizations.', 'resp_0da15b8ddfdb9bb4006940f1310d8c81a2a60417f9bba9fd81', NULL, '{"polled":true,"poll_status":"completed","jobId":"job_1765863730111_amqo467d2","status":"completed","responseId":"resp_0da15b8ddfdb9bb4006940f1310d8c81a2a60417f9bba9fd81","reportFormat":"Custom"}', '2025-12-16 05:42:09.940703'),
