('204', '81', 'assistant', '## Bank account validation during onboarding\n\n1) Validation step used\n- The onboarding flow employs a penny-drop (micro-deposit) verification to confirm the customer’s bank account details and ownership. The system indicates successful verification and proceeds once the account is validated. This verification is triggered during the bank details entry step in the onboarding flow and is followed by progression to subsequent steps once verification succeeds [1].\n\n2) How the verification is performed\n- The customer enters bank details (bank name, account number, etc.) and initiates a verification action (often labeled as sending a nominal amount, e.g., a penny cheque or ₹1). The platform validates this micro-deposit; upon successful verification, the user sees a Verified Bank Accounts screen and can continue with onboarding [1].\n\n3) Verification providers and scope\n- The documented flows describe in-app penny-drop verification as part of the onboarding process, without explicit reference to an external verification provider. The verification is embedded within the onboarding platform’s bank details workflow and aligns with the broader identity/KYC steps [1].\n\n4) Regulatory and KYC considerations\n- Bank account validation is integrated into the broader KYC-enabled onboarding flow. The process is linked to regulatory/compliance requirements around validating funding sources and ownership, with the onboarding sequence explicitly leading to KYC completion after bank verification (e.g., a screen or steps titled “Details Required to Finish KYC”) [1].\n\n\nSources\n\n[1] HSBC_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding V10.pdf\n[2] HSBC_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding V10.pdf', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Bank Details","payment details","Funding Account","Identity","KYC Compliance information","KYC UPDATION OVERDUE IN ACCOUNT","Bank comments","Com