('215', '82', 'user', 'How can a user track the progress of active campaigns and record specific feedback from customers?', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-12-16 07:23:12.609613');
INSERT INTO public.messages (id, thread_id, role, content, response_id, sources, metadata, created_at) VALUES
('216', '82', 'assistant', '## 1. Overview\n\nUsers should be able to:\n\n- View each active campaign’s status, progress vs. targets, and key KPIs on a campaign dashboard, using charts such as pie charts and deviation views already familiar from deviation & exposure widgets for portfolios and securities  .\n- Drill into a specific campaign to see milestones, underlying securities or products being promoted, and client-level engagement.\n- Log structured customer feedback (ratings, comments, sentiment, and channel) that is linked to both the campaign and the client account.\n- Use soft-stop style validations and alerts (similar to the list of soft stop deviations in order journeys) to ensure mandatory feedback fields and key compliance checks are met before saving or closing items  .\n\nThe design can reuse familiar patterns from the wealth order journey: dashboards for status (similar to Order Book), deviation/exposure visualizations, and soft/hard stop deviations for rule enforcement  .\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Model\n\n### 2.1 Campaign\nKey fields:\n- **CampaignId** (identifier)\n- **Name**\n- **Description**\n- **Objective / KPI definitions** (e.g., target AUM, number of leads, conversion rate)\n- **StartDate, EndDate**\n- **Status** (Planned, Active, On Hold, Completed, Cancelled)\n- **TargetSegments** (e.g., HNI segment, specific risk profiles)\n- **RelatedSecurities / Products** – link to security master or scheme master so KPIs can use existing holdings, asset class, and sector data used for deviation & exposure views  .\n- **OwnerRM / Team**\n- **Budget & Spend-to-date** (optional)\n\n### 2.2 CampaignProgress\nCaptures time-series progress and milestones:\n- **CampaignProgressId**\n- **CampaignId (FK)**\n- **AsOfDate**\n- **StatusSnapshot** (e.g., % complete, phase)\n- **KPI values** (e.g., number of contacts, meetings, proposals, orders placed, AUM influenced)\n- **DeviationFromTarget%** – analogous to portfolio deviation (actual vs. model vs. selected) used in deviation graphs ; here, compare *actual KPIs vs. target KPIs*.\n- **Milestone** (e.g., “Launched email blast”, “Completed RM meetings for Tier-1 clients”)\n\n### 2.3 CustomerFeedback\nFeedback at client and interaction level:\n- **FeedbackId**\n- **CampaignId (FK)**\n- **ClientId / InvestorId (FK)**\n- **InteractionDate**\n- **Channel** (Phone, In-person, Email, Portal, RM App, Event, etc.)\n- **Rating** (e.g., 1–5 or sentiment buckets: Positive/Neutral/Negative)\n- **SentimentScore** (derived or manually tagged)\n- **FeedbackComments**\n- **ProductsDiscussed / Securities** – linked to relevant securities or schemes if the feedback is about specific products, reusing security-level attributes like asset class and sector already used in exposure views  .\n- **NextAction** (Follow-up call, send proposal, do nothing, etc.)\n- **ActionOwner** (RM, Service team)\n- **Status** (Open, In Progress, Closed)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Screens and UX\n\n### 3.1 Campaign Dashboard\n\nPurpose: High-level monitoring of all active campaigns.\n\nCore elements:\n- **Campaign list / grid** showing:\n  - Campaign name, owner, segment\n  - Status and start/end dates\n  - High-level KPIs: e.g., #clients contacted, #orders, AUM influenced\n  - Visual indicator (e.g., traffic light or progress bar) for on-track / off-track based on deviation from targets.\n- **Aggregated charts**:\n  - **Pie chart** for distribution of active campaigns by segment, product type, or status.\n  - **Deviation-style chart** comparing *target vs. actual KPIs* across campaigns, reusing the concept of “model vs. actual vs. selected” from asset allocation graphs .\n- **Filters** by segment, RM, product, date range, and status.\n\nThink of this as the campaign-level equivalent of an Order Book, which lists all orders with their status against each order .\n\n### 3.2 Campaign Details Screen\n\nPurpose: Detailed view of a single campaign.\n\nSections:\n1. **Header** – Campaign summary (name, dates, owner, status, primary KPIs).\n2. **Progress & Deviation Widget**\n   - A **deviation graph** showing **target vs. actual vs. latest forecast** for core KPIs (e.g., “clients contacted”, “orders placed”, “AUM booked”), mirroring the model vs. actual vs. selected exposure widgets used for portfolios  .\n   - A **pie chart** for breakdown of responses by sentiment (positive/neutral/negative) or by product/security.\n3. **Milestone Timeline** – List of milestones from CampaignProgress.\n4. **Linked Orders / Transactions** – Show orders tagged as campaign-influenced, reusing the pattern from transaction and order displays where transaction date, number, and status are visible  .\n5. **Customer Feedback Tab** – Grid of feedback records with ability to filter by sentiment, RM, channel, etc.\n\n### 3.3 Feedback Capture Screen\n\nPurpose: Enable RMs or operations staff to log structured feedback after an interaction.\n\nAccess paths:\n- From **Campaign Details** (e.g., “Log Feedback” button).\n- From **Client / Investor 360** (select campaign + log feedback).\n\nFields:\n- Campaign (pre-selected when navigating from campaign)\n- Client / Account\n- Interaction date & time\n- Channel (LOV)\n- Rating & sentiment\n- Comment / notes\n- Products / securities discussed (multi-select linked to security master)\n- Next action & owner\n- Attachments (optional, e.g., meeting notes PDF)\n\nValidations:\n- Mandatory-field validation similar to order forms where mandatory fields marked with * must be filled before save .\n- **Soft-stop deviations** if key business rules are breached (e.g., missing sentiment for negative comments, missing next action for low rating), using the same concept as the *list of soft stop deviations* exposed in product cart overlays  .\n- **Hard-stop deviations** if minimal compliance requirements are not met (e.g., no client selected), blocking save until resolved, similar to existing hard-stop deviations on orders.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Workflows\n\n### 4.1 Create Campaign\n1. User navigates to Campaign Dashboard and selects **Create Campaign**.\n2. Enters campaign details (name, dates, segments, KPIs, target values, owner, budget).\n3. Selects related products/securities, drawing from security/scheme masters already used in product selection and exposure views  .\n4. System performs validations (dates, mandatory fields; optional soft stops for missing KPIs or segment definition).\n5. On success, campaign is created with status **Planned** or **Active**.\n\n### 4.2 Update Progress\n1. At defined intervals (daily/weekly), user or batch process creates **CampaignProgress** entries.\n2. KPIs are updated by:\n   - Auto-aggregating linked interactions (meetings, calls, portal logins) and orders tagged with the campaign; orders are already trackable with status at order level similar to Order Book views .\n   - Manual adjustments (e.g., event attendance count).\n3. The deviation widget recalculates **target vs. actual vs. forecast**, mirroring allocation deviation behavior.\n\n### 4.3 Log Feedback\n1. From either a client record or campaign, user selects **Log Feedback**.\n2. Feedback Capture screen opens with pre-filled campaign and optionally client.\n3. User fills mandatory fields; system raises soft-stop warnings if recommended data (e.g., sentiment) is missing.\n4. On save, feedback is:\n   - Linked to the campaign and client.\n   - Included in campaign sentiment charts and KPI calculations.\n\n### 4.4 Approve / Close Campaign\n1. When end date or KPI thresholds are reached, campaign moves to **Ready to Close**.\n2. Reviewer assesses KPIs, deviation from targets, and feedback summary.\n3. Reviewer approves closure; campaign status updated to **Completed**.\n4. System freezes further structural changes but still allows post-campaign reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Validation Rules and Soft/Hard Stops\n\nReusing patterns from order journeys where product cart overlays highlight hard-stop and soft-stop deviations for an order  :\n\n- **Hard Stops (block action)**:\n  - Create Campaign: missing mandatory fields (name, dates, owner, at least one KPI).\n  - Log Feedback: missing client, campaign, basic comment or rating.\n- **Soft Stops (allow override with warning)**:\n  - Campaign without defined target KPIs.\n  - Feedback with low rating but no next action defined.\n\nThe UI can present these as a **“list of hard stop deviations”** and **“list of soft stop deviations”** in a deviations panel, parallel to existing order deviation patterns.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Reporting and Analytics\n\n### 6.1 Campaign Performance Reports\n\n- **Campaign Summary report**: status, duration, target vs. actual KPIs, deviation %, linked orders/AUM.\n- **Segment & Product performance**: break down by client segment and by security/asset class using existing asset-class and sector categorization logic already used in exposure widgets  .\n\n### 6.2 Feedback Trend Reports\n\n- **Sentiment over time** per campaign.\n- **Channel effectiveness**: KPIs by interaction channel.\n- **RM performance**: feedback ratings by RM or team.\n\nVisuals:\n- Pie charts for sentiment distribution, channel mix, and positive/negative feedback ratio.\n- Line or bar charts for KPI progression vs. targets.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Integration, Security, and Audit\n\n### 7.1 Integration Touchpoints\n\n- **CRM / Marketing tools**:\n  - Import campaign definitions and target client lists.\n  - Sync interaction events (emails sent, opens, clicks, event attendance).\n- **Order and portfolio systems**:\n  - Tag orders as campaign-influenced.\n  - Use existing security and scheme masters for product associations and asset/sector breakdowns, similar to the deviation & exposure and security holdings views  fileciteturn0file18.\n\n### 7.2 Security Roles\n\n- **Campaign Owner / RM** – create and update campaigns they own; log and edit feedback for their clients.\n- **Operations / Marketing Admin** – manage master data, approve/close campaigns.\n- **View-only roles** – view dashboards and reports but cannot modify campaigns or feedback.\n\n### 7.3 Audit Considerations\n\n- Maintain **audit trails** for:\n  - Campaign creation, modification, and closure (who, what, when).\n  - Feedback creation and edits.\n  - Changes to KPI targets and thresholds.\n- Log overrides where users proceed despite soft-stop warnings, similar to how soft-stop deviations may be overridden in order flows.\n\n---\n\n## 8. How Users Track Progress and Capture Feedback in Practice\n\n1. **Daily/Weekly Monitoring**\n   - User opens the Campaign Dashboard to see all active campaigns, their status, and high-level KPIs with deviation indicators and charts.\n2. **Drill-Down**\n   - For a specific campaign, user opens Campaign Details to check detailed KPI progress, deviation graphs, milestone history, orders, and feedback distribution.\n3. **Field-Level Feedback Capture**\n   - After each client interaction, RM logs feedback via the Feedback Capture screen, ensuring mandatory fields are filled and resolving or accepting any soft-stop warnings.\n4. **Closing the Loop**\n   - At the end of the campaign, the owner and approver review performance and feedback trends before closing, with all key actions and deviations audited.\n\nThis design lets users manage campaigns end-to-end while reusing proven UX and validation patterns from existing wealth order, deviation, and exposure journeys.\n\n\n### Sources\n\n[1] 360ONE_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV13_Part 1.pdf  \n[2] SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V10_SBI_CCV13.pdf  \n[3] SBI_Journey of Client Portal_Order Placement_V10_CCV11.pdf  \n[4] HSBC_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV10_Part 1.pdf  \n[5] 360ONE_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV13_Part 3.pdf', 'd76a1db5-04aa-4e7c-b146-e1132c549c20', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["RM","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","Mutual Funds","Field Level Details","Portfolio Performance Report","pie chart","Minimum Amount/Unit Validation"],"seed_node_ids":["report:pf_performance_report","system:rmws","dataentity:field_level_details","report:pie_chart","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:rm","dataentity:transaction","dataentity:order","dataentity:customer","report:minimum_amount_unit_validation","report:field_level_details"],"expanded_nodes":63,"expanded_edges":128,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: d76a1db5-04aa-4e7c-b146-e1132c549c20\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user track the progress of active campaigns and record specific feedback from customers?","How can a user monitor the status and performance of active campaigns and capture customer feedback within the platform, including required data fields and workflows?","Provide guidance on tracking active campaigns'' progress and recording customer feedback within the wealth-management platform. Include: how to view campaign status, milestones, and KPIs; capture customer feedback (ratings, comments, sentiment, channel) linked to specific campaigns and client accounts; data models (Campaign, CampaignProgress, CustomerFeedback), screens (Campaign Dashboard, Campaign Details, Feedback Capture), workflows (Create Campaign, Update Progress, Log Feedback, Approve/Close Campaign), validation rules, reporting options (Campaign Performance Reports, Feedback Trends), integration touchpoints with CRM/marketing tools, security roles, and audit considerations.","Previous context ID: d76a1db5-04aa-4e7c-b146-e1132c549c20\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: How can a user track the progress of active campaigns and record specific feedback from customers? pie chart","Previous context ID: d76a1db5-04aa-4e7c-b146-e1132c549c20\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to 