('184', '78', 'assistant', 'Actions to test campaign communications prior to broadcasting, as evidenced in the documented campaign workflows:\n\n1) Create and stage the campaign in Campaign Creation and Campaign Management workflows. This phase supports drafting and organizing the campaign content before any deployment, enabling pre-broadcast validation and alignment with objectives. [1]\n\n2) Review Campaign Admin details to verify the campaign manager responsible for the broadcast and to confirm the selected target audience (target list). This helps ensure the correct recipients are chosen and that accountability is clear before sending. [1]\n\n3) Inspect Campaign Notes to view the actual content of the messages that will be sent (e.g., Email and/or SMS). This provides content validation against branding, tone, and compliance expectations prior to any broadcast. [1]\n\n4) Use the content view/preview capability embedded in the campaign notes or admin screens to visually validate how messages will render to recipients before deployment. This preview step is implied by the ability to view message content within the campaign management flow. [1]\n\nIn short, the documented process emphasizes three core actions—campaign creation/staging, administrative review of ownership and audience, and content viewing/previews—to test campaign communications before they are broadcasted. [1][2]\n\nSources:\n- JBR_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV10docx.pdf\n- JBR_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_JioBlackRock_V1_CCV1docx.pdf', 'resp_0c5ec1f943dff3bb00693f021f163081a29cbb5a910126e9fa', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["No. of Installments should be greater than or equal to SIP/STP/SWP Min. No of Installments","Obs 16","Amount redemption - Validate Amount only","Full redemption - No validation","Validate that it should be in multiples of 1","pass the “Y” Flag in close AC field","don’t send the amount/unit in outbound file/API"