('198', '81', 'assistant', 'Handover vs Delegation: a concise functional distinction\n\n- What they are\n  - Handover: permanent reassignment of ownership and management of Prospects and Customers from one Agent to another. Typically used when an Agent exits or a customer requests a change of Agent [1].\n  - Delegation: temporary assignment that allows another Agent to act on behalf of the owner without transferring ownership; used when an Agent’s movement is temporary (e.g., vacation) [2].\n\n- When to apply\n  - Use Handover when the relationship ownership should permanently move to a new Agent (or RM) due to staffing changes or customer requests [1].\n  - Use Delegation for temporary coverage while the original Agent is unavailable or when a short-term workload transfer is needed, with the expectation that ownership remains with the original Agent [2].\n\n- Ownership vs access\n  - Handover transfers ownership and ongoing responsibility for the customer relationship to the receiving Agent; the original owner is no longer the primary owner of those relationships [1].\n  - Delegation grants temporary permission for another Agent to perform actions on behalf of the owner, without changing ultimate ownership or long-term responsibility [2].\n\n- Triggers and authorization/logging\n  - Handover requires explicit authorization and is a formal, typically supervisory-approved change of ownership (e.g., in Maybank’s workflow) [1].\n  - Delegation is designed to be auto-authorized in the system for temporary coverage, enabling quick reallocation of tasks without a formal ownership change [2].\n\n- Data access and scope\n  - Both mechanisms apply to Leads, Prospects, and Clients associated with the Agent hierarchy, but the effect differs: Handover changes who “owns” and manages the relationship; Delegation changes who can perform actions on behalf of the owner while ownership remains with the original Agent [1][2].\n\n- Compliance and continuity\n  - Handover ensures continuity of long-term client management under new ownership when staffing changes occur, with formal tracking of ownership changes for compliance purposes [1].\n  - Delegation ensures continuity of client service during temporary absences, maintaining coverage while preserving the original ownership and accountability structures, with automatic authorization to minimize downtime [2].\n\nSources\n- Maybank_Handover and Delegation_V12_CCV10.pdf\n- HSBC_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf', '9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Supervisor Approval screen","To Approve tab","Wealth Qube","WAT","User Office","Relationship","Folio Master","Portfolio Master","account master","Customer Dashboard"],"seed_node_ids":["system:user_office","report:performance_projection","system:to_approve_tab","datastore:folio_master","report:customer_dashboard","datastore:pf_master","system:wat","dataentity:folio","dataentity:relationship","system:supervisor_approval_screen","datastore:account_master","system:wealth_qube"],"expanded_nodes":46,"expanded_edges":51,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identify what they refer to based on the conversation history\\n• Internally clarify the question to make it self-contained and explicit\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Focused Response Generation:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related informat