('212', '82', 'assistant', '## How a user automatically generates a targeted lead list based on customer criteria\n\n### 1. Core capability\nThe platform supports **Automatic Lead Generation**, where leads are automatically identified from existing customers in the wealth system once the user defines filter criteria in a **Lead Rule / Lead Criteria** setup. The system then filters customer records and produces a list of potential targets for campaigns  .\n\n### 2. Where the user starts (Lead List Management)\nUnder the **Campaign / Lead List Management** area, the user can manage target-audience lists via three options: Automatic Lead Generation, Lead Upload, and Manual Lead Creation. For automatic generation, the user selects the **Lead Rule / Lead Criteria** function  .\n\n### 3. Defining the customer criteria (Lead Rule / Lead Criteria setup)\nIn the **Lead Rule** (or **Lead Criteria**) screen, the user:\n\n1. **Adds or opens a Lead Rule**: The user can add a new rule, view, or modify an existing rule  .\n2. **Configures filters on existing customers**: The rule encapsulates the filter logic applied on customer records stored in the wealth system. Typical filters can include (conceptually):\n   - Demographics (e.g., age band, location, customer type)\n   - Asset and AUM characteristics (e.g., total AUM range, holdings in certain products)\n   - Risk profile and investment preferences (e.g., risk category, product risk vs customer risk alignment)\n   - Engagement or lifecycle status (e.g., existing customers without recent transactions, customers in a certain segment)\n3. **Saves the rule** so it can be reused and re-run to regenerate updated lead lists as data changes.\n\nThe rule definition is the central place where the user translates business targeting logic into system-usable filters over the wealth customer base  .\n\n### 4. Automatic generation of the lead list\nOnce a rule is defined:\n\n1. The user chooses **Generate List** against the selected Lead Rule  .\n2. The system **queries existing customer records** in the wealth platform using the rule’s filters (demographics, assets, risk, behavior, etc.).\n3. The system **returns only those customers that satisfy the criteria** as the output list. These become the **automatically generated leads** linked to that rule.\n\nThis process converts static rules into a dynamic, data-driven target list sourced from the underlying customer, risk, holdings, and product data referenced in the platform’s maintenance and CRM modules .\n\n### 5. Working with the generated lead list\nAfter generation, the user can:\n\n- Use the list as the **target audience for a campaign**, leveraging the campaign module that is explicitly linked to the suspect-to-lead journey  .\n- Optionally export or integrate the list to downstream CRM or engagement tools (e.g., email, calling, RM worklists), depending on the platform’s configured integrations.\n\nLead rules remain available for **view, modification, and re-use**, enabling recurring or refreshed target lists without redefining criteria each time  .\n\n---\n\n### Direct answer\nA user automatically generates a list of target leads by navigating to the campaign/lead management area, opening **Lead Rule / Lead Criteria** setup, defining the desired customer filters over existing wealth customers (e.g., demographic, asset, risk, or engagement criteria), saving the rule, and then using the **Generate List** action. The system applies the rule to the wealth customer base, filters matching records, and produces a reusable lead list that can be directly used as the campaign target set or exported to connected CRM/engagement channels  .\n\n### Sources\n1. [1] 360One_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV10docx.pdf\n2. [2] HSBC_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV13docx.pdf\n3. [3] 360One_Audit Trail_V10_CCV10.pdf', 'd76a1db5-04aa-4e7c-b146-e1132c549c20', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["Lead","Filters","Custome