('223', '84', 'assistant', '### How an Operations User can bulk transfer many clients to a new agent without selecting them individually\n\nAn Operations User can transfer a large number of clients to a new agent in one go by using the **bulk Client Handover via file upload** on the Relationship area of the platform, rather than selecting each client in the UI. This is achieved through the following mechanism:\n\n1. **Use the Relationship → File Upload function**  \n   - Navigate to the Relationship (or equivalent) module/menu.  \n   - Choose **File Upload** from this menu. \n\n2. **Select the bulk handover upload type**  \n   - In the File Upload screen, set **Upload Type = Client Handover** (or similarly named option).  \n   - This upload type is specifically designed to **reassign ownership of multiple client relationships in bulk from one agent to another**.   \n\n3. **Prepare and upload the batch file**  \n   - Prepare a structured file (typically CSV/XLSX) containing, at minimum, identifiers for:  \n     - The clients/relationships to be moved (e.g., client ID / relationship ID), and  \n     - The **new agent/RM** to which they should be reassigned.  \n   - Upload this file under the **Client Handover** upload type.  \n   - On successful upload, the system processes all listed records and applies the ownership change in bulk; **no per‑client manual selection is required in the UI**.  \n\n4. **Review results in the error or upload log**  \n   - After upload, the Operations User can review the **error log/upload log** to confirm which records were successfully handed over and which (if any) failed due to validation issues (e.g., invalid IDs, status constraints).   \n\n5. **Authorization / approval behavior**  \n   - Bulk Client Handover uploads **do not typically require a separate authorization step**; once the file is uploaded successfully, the handover is effected automatically (though this may be configurable per implementation).   \n   - Where an approval workflow is configured for handover actions generally, such items would appear in an authorization or **Pending Approval**–type queue for an Operations checker to review and approve, similar to how other items move from a common **Pending Approval Listing** into a user‑specific approval queue. \n\n### Direct, minimal answer\n\nTo transfer a large number of clients to a new agent without selecting them individually, the Operations User should use the **bulk Client Handover file upload** under the Relationship module, selecting upload type **Client Handover**, uploading a batch file listing all affected clients and the new agent, then verifying the outcome via the error/upload log; this avoids any need for per‑client selection in the UI.   \n\n---\n\n#### Sources\n\n[1] Maybank_Handover and Delegation_V12_CCV10.pdf   \n[2] HSBC_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf   \n[3] JBR_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf   \n[4] SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V10_SBI_CCV13.pdf ', 'd91b121e-5ac3-40dd-897b-23e557cf2ff5', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["User Office","Pending Approval Listing","Supervisor Approval screen","To Approve tab","Batch File","Entitlements","System generated mail","External Systems","Product Cart","Channel Partner"],"seed_node_ids":["datastore:product_cart","system:generated_mail","system:user_office","dataentity:pending_approval_listing","system:external_systems","datastore:batch_file","dataentity:product_cart","dataentity:entitlements","datastore:pending_approval_listing","system:product_cart","system:supervisor_approval_screen","system:pms_app","report:performance_projection","report:product_cart","system:to_approve_tab","dataentity:channel_partner"],"expanded_nodes":95,"expanded_edges":248,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY inform