('225', '84', 'assistant', '### Bank account validation step during onboarding\n\nDuring the wealth onboarding and investment account opening process, the customer’s bank account details are validated through a **bank‑validation API call** triggered from the Bank Details section of the onboarding journey.\n\n#### How the validation works\n\n- On the **Bank Details** screen, the customer selects or enters their savings account number as a mandatory field.[1]\n- Once the account is selected, the system **fetches associated data** (e.g., IFSC, account holder name, branch name, bank city) from the backend/banking source rather than relying solely on user‑input, ensuring that the details are consistent with the bank’s records.[1]\n- A dedicated **“Bank Validation API” is invoked** for the selected account, explicitly noted as “Bank Validation API need to be called” in the Bank Details field‑level specification.[1]\n- This API call serves as the primary control to verify that:\n  - The bank account is valid and active.\n  - The IFSC and branch details correspond correctly to the account.\n  - The account holder details match the customer’s profile (ownership/name consistency).\n\nThe validation is part of the broader e‑KYC and account‑opening flow, where bank details are captured immediately after PAN and before completion of KYC details and document upload.[2]\n\n#### Nature of the validation\n\n- The documentation specifies a **bank‑validation API**, not micro‑deposits, ACH trial transactions, or external third‑party account‑link providers.[1]\n- The check is **real‑time, API‑based**, aligned with KYC/ISA opening prerequisites that require a registered PAN and an existing savings account.[1]\n- This step supports **STP** by programmatically confirming that the mapped bank account is correct and usable for subsequent investment transactions (payments, redemptions, SIPs) as part of the same onboarding journey.[1][2]\n\n#### Where the control is governed\n\n- **Screen/control**: The validation is governed by the **Bank Details section** of the investment/wealth account opening (ISA opening) flow in the client portal or mobile onboarding journey.[1][2]\n- **Data source**: The API draws on **core banking / bank systems** to fetch and validate IFSC, branch, and account‑holder information against the entered/selected account number.[1]\n- **KYC/regulatory alignment**: Bank validation is embedded in the e‑KYC and account‑opening sequence (PAN → Bank Details → KYC details → document upload → e‑sign), ensuring that only customers with a valid, verified bank account and KYC‑compliant status proceed to full wealth account activation.[1][2]\n\nIn summary, the **single, explicit validation step** for verifying a customer’s bank account during onboarding is a **backend bank‑validation API call initiated from the Bank Details screen**, which programmatically confirms the correctness and ownership alignment of the account details before the onboarding can be completed.[1]\n\n---\n\n#### Sources\n\n- [1] SBI_Journey of Client Portal_KYC_ISA Opening_V10_CCV11.pdf \n- [2] HSBC_DIY_Journey of Customer Onboarding V10.pdf ', 'd91b121e-5ac3-40dd-897b-23e557cf2ff5', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["KYC Compliance information","screen to show the Validations and Warning","Validations and Warning","System would validate if KYC status in Customer Profile Details is other than “KYC REGISTERED” or “UNDER PROCESS” there would be a hard stop","Wealth Qube","WAT","HSBC PWS"],"seed_node_ids":["compliance:kyc_compliance_info","dataentity:validations_warning","compliance:would_validate_if_kyc_status_customer_profile_details_is_other_than_kyc_registered_or_under_process_there_would_be_a_hard_stop","system:wealth_qube","compliance:validations","report:screen_to_show_validations_warning","system:hsbc_pws","system:wat"],"expanded_nodes":62,"expanded_edges":123,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: d91b121e-5ac3-40dd