('237', '86', 'assistant', 'Types of planning goals in wealth-management planning\n\n- Wealth Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Grow Wealth; Preserve Wealth [2]\n- Retirement Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Retirement [2]\n- Education Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Education [2]\n- Protection Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Death and Disability; Critical Illness; Hospitalization and Health; Legacy Tax; Credit Life; Property [2]\n- Tax Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Tax [2]\n- Execution Planning goals [1]\n  - Sub-goals / milestones: Not explicitly listed in the available extract; plan-type label exists [2]\n\nHow many goals can be planned for one customer?\n- Documented guidance does not specify a hard maximum number of goals per client. The available materials describe a goal-centric view where a user can see a summary of all goals mapped to a particular customer, indicating support for multiple goals per client [3]. Additionally, goal creation includes input such as a start date and a time horizon, implying the ability to create goals with varying scopes and timelines [4]. Based on the cited materials, there is no explicit cap published in the documents.\n\nGoals in the planning workflow (prioritization/grouping)\n- The materials describe a goal summary and the ability to plan for multiple goals per customer, with a dedicated workflow for planning financial goals and investments. However, explicit prioritization rules or grouping policies within the planning workflow are not described in the cited extracts [3].\n\nSources\n- [1] SBI_Journey of Launching a New Product_V12.pdf\n- [2] SBI_Journey of Launching a New Product_V12.pdf\n- [3] Maybank_Journey of Self-Assessment and Supervisor Assessment-Customer Dashboard_V12_CCV_V10docx.pdf\n- [4] Maybank_Journey of Defining Maintenances_V11_CCV10.pdf', '127aa6be-6579-432a-84d3-5b0585421bd6', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["goals","Goal (ACC)","retirement","education"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:education","dataentity:goal_acc","dataentity:goals","dataentity:retirement"],"expanded_nodes":4,"expanded_edges":0,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what are different type of goals we can take up for planning? How many goals can be planned for one customer?","What types of planning goals can be defined for a client in wealth management, and what is the allowed or recommended number of goals per client?","In wealth-management planning, what goal categories are supported (e.g., retirement, education, major purchases, liquidity needs, risk management, estate planning), what sub-goals or milestones exist, and are there any system or policy constraints on how many goals can be created for a single customer, and how are goals prioritized or grouped within a planning workflow?","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: what are different type of goals we can take up for planning? How many goals can be planned for one customer? education","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instruction