('243', '88', 'assistant', '# Lead RM Sorting & Ranking Logic\n\n## Primary sorting metric\n- The lead performer data for RMs is sorted primarily by Assets Under Management (AUM) in descending order. This is explicitly described as sorting the RM’s customer list by descending AUM, effectively ranking RMs by the size of their managed assets (AUM) within the dashboard views. [1][2]\n\n## Data organization and grouping\n- Data for each RM is presented with customers grouped by Sub Product Type, and within those groups, the list is sorted by AUM in descending order. This structure emphasizes higher-asset segments first within each Sub Product Type category. [1]\n\n## Data scope and exclusions\n- Non-wealth customers are excluded from RM dashboards by default. When a client is not wealth-eligible, the system uses a Vacant RM placeholder to ensure these accounts do not appear in RM dashboards, effectively excluding them from lead performer rankings. This exclusion logic is described in the RM dashboard context. [2]\n\n## Data sources and scope of metrics\n- The ranking relies on portfolio data tied to customer accounts and their product holdings, focusing on primary wealth customers as the basis for AUM calculations and ranking. Currency-level views (AUM by Currency) are available, indicating the data can be segmented by currency for cross-border or multi-currency portfolios. [2]\n\n## Filters and search capabilities (as documented)\n- The RM dashboards provide a search capability by Customer Name, enabling quick drill-down within the sorted lead data. This supports identifying a specific client within the descending-AUM ordering. [1]\n- Dashboards also expose filters related to RM and other lead-related views, though explicit region, product-line, or time-period sorting weights are not described in the cited materials. The primary documented filtering/interaction centers on RM selection and customer search within the AUM-ordered lists. [1][2]\n\n## Tie-breakers and alternative ranking rules\n- The available documentation specifies the primary sorting criterion (AUM in descending order) and the grouping by Sub Product Type, but does not document a secondary tie-break rule (e.g., by number of clients, recency, or revenue rate) beyond this. Therefore, no explicit tie-breaker beyond the AUM-based sort is described in the sources. [1][2]\n\n## Summary\n- Sorting and ranking of RMs for lead performer data is centered on the primary metric of AUM (desc). Data is organized by Sub Product Type and supports customer search within the sorted view. Non-wealth customers are excluded via a Vacant RM mechanism to keep lead data focused on wealth clientele. Currency breakdowns exist as additional data views. [1][2]\n\n### Sources\n- HSBC_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V10_CCV10.pdf [1]\n- SAAB-Journey of Self_Assessment and Supervisor Assessment_RM Dashboard_V10_CCV10docx.pdf [2]', '306c4b47-c484-4061-a8b3-6c47c75e290f', NULL, '{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["RM","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","Field Level Details","Portfolio Performance Report","pie chart","Minimum Amount/Unit Validation","Systematic Running Status Report"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:rm","dataentity:order","dataentity:transaction","report:field_level_details","system:rmws","report:pie_chart","report:minimum_amount_unit_validation","dataentity:customer","report:pf_performance_report","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:field_level_details","report:systematic_running_status_report"],"expanded_nodes":99,"expanded_edges":283,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data?","Describe the criteria and method used to rank and display Relationship Managers (RMs) when presenting lead performer data.","What sorting criteria and ranking logic are applied to order Relationship Managers (RMs) when displaying lead performer data, including the primary performance metrics, weighting scheme, tie-breakers, data sources, and applicable filters (e.g., region, product line, time period) used for the display in dashboards or reports?","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data? Validations","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data? Bank comments","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data? Product Cart","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data? Prerequisite","[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser''s Question: What logic is used to sort the RMs when we need to show the lead performer data? Customer Dashboard","Order CONTAINS PMS application","Wealth Qube PROCESSES Order","Mutual Funds VALIDATES Order","Systematic Cancelled Date CONTAINS RM"],"kg_vector_store_id":"vs_6934751b8a90819190113fe85b689848","doc_vector_store_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","intent_route":"hybrid","intent_hops":2,"domain":"wealth_management","vectorstore_id":"vs_6910a0f29b548191befd180730d968ee","response_id":"306c4b47-c484-4061-a8b3-6c47c75e290f","is_conversational":false,"processing_time_seconds":82.81,"request_id":"85b3